right engine thrust reverser stayed deployed after touchdown and thrust reverser handle stowed. shutdown engine on taxi in. nr 2 engine inbd sleeve failed to stow. open. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : other part name : thrust reverser part condition : malfunctioned

reverse thrust lever has lost motion, no thrust reverser operation engine 1 found nr 1 engine outboard thrust reverser lower actuator and sync lock inop. right & right nr 1 engine outboard lower thrust reverser actuator and lower sync lock ref amm 78-31-03, also right & right upper and lower sync shafts ref amm 78-31-04, deployed and stowed nr 1 engine thrust reverser several times, ops and leak chks nomal. ok for service. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : none part name : actuator part condition : faulty

inflight shutdown & diversion - due to status messages right engine sec cont and right engine pri cont came on at fl370. during climb to fl390 thrust levers advanced all engine parameters red lined and engine unresponsive to throttle commands a loud bang and yaw w as experienced, followed qrh and shutdown right engine. removed and replaced the nr 2 engine ref cards.

right engine shutdown in-flight due to engine valve eicas and engine surge. crew reports engine windmilled for approximately 7-10minutes with pos itive oil pressure. replaced the nr 2 engine iaw amm 71-00-02. nature of condition : warning indication, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : engine part condition : surges

inflight shutdown & air turn back - due to the loss of the nr 1 engine. at approximately 600ft above ground level, flight crew reported left engine compressor stall and engine roll back. crew followed qrh and shutdown engine. maintenance found turbine damage. the engine was replaced.

aircraft was grounded. emergency declared. nrt dfw flight diverted to sea account crew shutdown the number two engine after overheat fire indications ( engine fail right, turb ovt sensor engine right, fire engine right, bleed off engine right ) and high vibrations. single engine time was approximately 150 minutes. the fire light extinguished after the engine was shutdown and the fire handle was pulled. however the fire bottles were not discharged. the flight diverted to sea and landed without further incident. upon initial inspection, numerous blades in the low pressure turbine section were found damaged. removed and replaced right engine per work card 71-28-17. leak and operational check good. nature of condition : vibration buffet, warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : engine part condition : overheated
diverted to tlh due to left engine compressor stall. the engine was shutdown. maintenance found turbine damage and the left external fuel tank engine was replaced.

ship 9573 - the crew experienced an engine surge and high exhaust temperatures with the #2 engine so the flight diverted to cae. the pilot did reduce power on the problem engine since that engine did not recover from the surge. the qrh directed to shutdown the #2 engine. the flight descended to fl200 and declared an emergency with air traffic control for the diversion. upon arrival, maintenance found metal in the tailpipe. corrective action : the #2 engine was replaced. ( lp #3823804 ) nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : engine shutdown, unsched landing part name : engine part condition : surges

right engine compressor stalled, followed by engine vibration high. shutdown the engine. engine change in work. nature of condition : warning indication, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : compressor part condition : stalled
performed an air turn back due to a right engine compressor stall. the engine was at idle at touch down. maintenance right eported turbine damage and the engine was replaced.

crew reported that the right engine was unresponsive on approach. shut the engine down at 20k during decent. the right engine ine did not respond. engine was stuck at idle. the engine began creeping up to 1.4 engine pressure ratio, which was too much for landing. the flight crew elected to shutdown the right engine. maintenance found the throttle flex cable disconnected at aft the throttle quadrant in the aft cargo bin. replaced the flex cable, ran engine, and operation check normal.

inflight shutdown & air turn back - the crew returned the aircraft back to departure following the failure of the #1 engine. the left engine ex perienced a compressor stall on takeoff, with the exhaust gas temperature reaching 800 degrees, and then the #1 engine rolled back. the engine was shutdown and secured by the flight crew per the qrh. : maintenance replaced engine.

right engine compressor stalled in cruise at 18000ft, rolled back to zero thrust, complied with qrh, the engine was shutdown followed by a right engine system fail. borescope found compressor damage. engine changed. nature of condition : warning indication, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : compressor part condition : failed

air turn back inflight shutdown - returned to atl due to right engine compressor stalls with vibrations at top of climb. pulled the engine back to idle. crew followed qrh and shutdown engine due to vibrations. emergency declared. maintenance found metal in tail pipe and turbine damage. the right engine was replaced.

inflight shutdown declared emergency, nr 1 engine throttle stuck in cruise position physically would not move aft engine inflight. right & right nr 1 engine main engine control per amm. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : mec part condition : faulty

ship 187 - inflight shutdown & diversion into bos due to right engine loss of oil pressure. ca accomplished qrh checklist engine oil pressure followed by engine failure or shutdown checklist, shutting down #2 engine. emergency declared with air traffic control. main tenance found metal in oil filter and on mcds. corrective action : replaced engine

left engine oil pressure light and low left engine oil pressure. oil qty zero. shutdown left engine. emergency declared. found oil pressure line that feeds intermediate bearing leaking out from behind sleeve area. replaced left side engine ip lp turbine oil tube and tube sleeve. serviced oil to proper level used total of 27 qts of oil during the operation of run up. run up engine to power for total of 65 minutes, no leak found, engine oil qty was steady between 20 and 21 qts. during the complete engine operation. nature of condition : warning indication, fluid loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : sleeve part condition : leaking

nr 2 engine with severe damage after takeoff, strong bang noise and aircraft vibration, the engine was secured with engine severe damage check list. the engine was removed and replaced. the engine was removed and replaced. nature of condition : engine stoppage precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : engine part condition : damaged

open - etops significant system - during descent w both throttles at idle stops right engine power was significantly higher than lt engine power. at fl 250 left engine n1 = 31.8 ; right engine n1 = 46.7. left engine n2 = 65.2 %, right engine n2 = 79.8 % ( cont ) ( continued ) at fl 250, idle descent : egts ( both ) = 323 * fuel flow : left engine = 0.6, right engine = 1.4 power difference at idle stops went away at 10,000 '. autopilot and autothrottle were on during event. no thrust differences observed during any other phases of flight. thrust diff erence only noted from descent from cruise altitude to 10,000. during trouble shooting found connector d766 flight ground idle sel on nr 2 engine dirty and loose. cleaned and re-attached secured. performed engine control system test ( amm 76-11-00

ea 7830-02252 rev a. during thrust reverser inspection found nr 2 engine inboard thrust reverser nr9 cascade broken - missing and support ring broken with parts missing. ref st engine nr 0065467. removed and installed nr 2 engine inboard thrust reverser cascades segments iaw am m 78-31-05-404, disc placed and installed lower heat-shield nr 2 engine inboard thrust reverser to fom iaw engine manual rb211 78-31-25 removed and installed nr 2 engine inboard thrust reverser support ring iaw amm 78-31 - 28-004, 78-31-28-404. work was accomplished on st engine nr 0 06546 7 and inspected.

discrepancy : at top of descent, autothrottle moved throttles to idle, nr 1 engine made " pop " noise and shutdown. prior to top of descent, engine indications were normal. performed engine failure qrh. was able to restart engine and perform normal landing. submitted engine trend report in-flight. corrective action : performed troubleshooting iaw amm 71-00-42. removed and replaced nr 1 engine fuel filters iaw amm 73-11-02, no findings borescope of nr 1 engine accomplished iaw amm 72-00-00 stages 1, 3, and 8 by bsi. results on file. remove and replace nr 1 engine mec iaw amm 73-21-01-401, no leaks found on mec or nr 1 engine fuel filters. accomplished idle checks, accelerate decelerate check iaw amm 71-00, ok for service at this tim

the flight retuned to cun and an uneventful single engine landing. the nr 1 engine stalled and failure shortly after. the flight crew heard the left engine popping and felt a shudder during the climb out. this was accompanied by engine parameters rolling back. the nr 1 engine was shutdown, per the qrh. corrective action : maintenance found meta left in the tailpipe upon arrival back at the gate. the engine was replaced.

air turn back, inflight shutdown nr 1 engine experienced loud bang then rolled back during departure. approximately 3000 feet msl max takeoff thrust, flap20, 200kias. engine continued to windmill, did not attempt restart. appeared to be a light vibration during remainder off light. visual inspection of inlet & exhaust of nr 1 engine. found metal in tail pipe. require engine change. nature of condition : partial rpm power loss, vibration buffet precautionary procedure : dump fuel, emer. descent, engine shutdown part name : engine part condition : making metal

aircraft behind unsatisfactory during taxi for takeoff reported tailpipe fire. shutdown engine #1 in accordance with checklist. gr ounded - yes. upon arrival to aircraft flight crew stated all engine 1 parameters were normal. accomplished engine vents and drains inspection of #1 engine iaw b737-900 amm 71-71-00-200-810-f00 no defects noted. oil consumption rates at engine # 1 and engine #2 are within limits. performed #1 engine idle power leak check per amm 71-00-00-700-801-f00 operation check good no defect noted

after both engine start, right engine eicas message & right pack off as right engine bleed off could not establish duct pressure to the right duct. after defering high pressure shut off valve, right engine has no bleed air. removed right engine pressure shutoff valve iaw amm jc-11-09. right engine high pressure shut off valve right thrust reverser remains activated, removed and replaced the right engine air supply control card. didn ' t fix the fault. removed and replaced pressure shutoff valve on # 2 engine iaw amm 36-11-09. leak check and operation check good at this time.

ship 6802 - inflight shutdown diversion - flight crew diverted to syr due to lost oil pressure on right engine. qrh was followed and engine was shutdown. corrective action : visually inspected inlet and exhaust - no trouble found ( n1 will turn by hand ). inspected right engine chip detectors - no trouble found. maintenance unable to turn n2 through gearbox turn pad, engine change required. right engine was replaced and aircraft rts. engine changed on logpage 1373023.

nr 2 engine failed at 2000 feet on takeoff. mi at 1705 feet during climb, loud noise from nr 2 engine, no engine pressure ratio, smoke in cockpit, and engine vibration. nr 2 engine had a failure of multiple stages of the turbine section. the engine and thrust reverser were removed and replaced. the engine seizure phase 2 conditional inspection was performed iaw amm 05-51-61and the parts departs airplane conditional inspection was accomplished iaw amm 05-51-59. nature of condition : smoke fumes odors sparks, vibration buffet, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : engine shutdown, emer. descent, unsched landing part name : engine part condition : failed

climbing thru fl340 with engines all at climb power we felt a bump like minor turbulence. then another and another. we saw engine 2 n1 fluctuating so we suspected a compressor stall. as we were running the qrh for engine compressor stall we right eceived level 2 engine 2 loop a. we then ran engine 2 loop a checklist before finishing the compressor stall checklist. the engine loop checklist indicated no fire. the compressor stall checklist had unsatisfactory advance #2 engine slowly. all indications were normal so we elected to leave #2 at idle thru landing rollout. #2 engine replaced shgn 17apr20 18 : 38 indicator installed #2 engine ref work card 71t1701 work

during the landing roll with thrust reversers deployed nr 1 engine failed. grounded - yes. inspected & found 5th stage check valve stuck open. replaced check valve. leak checked good, ref amm 36-11-02. accomplished test 5 power assurance check. test engine limits good 65, 70, 75 % n1. during throttle back engine compressor stalled at approximately 60 % n1 with exhaust gas temperature 560 center, advanced throttle. compressor stall ended but repeated again when reducing throttle. was able to prevent stall by slowly reducing to idle, ref amm task 71-00-700-813-f00. replaced nr 1 engine per tc 78471000 & 78471001. ran engine, no defects noted. nature of condition : engine flame out precautionary procedure : other part name : engine part condition : failed

crew performed a rejected takeoff due to no right engine throttle response from idle. found right engine inboard sleeve middle locking actuator broken and bad resolver input to electronic engine controllers. replaced middle locking actuator iaw amm 78-31. performed, tested and engine ine run with confirmed increase of engine pressure ratio. ok for service.

during cruise at fl 400, the left engine overheated to 910 degrees with power retarded. diverted, declared emergency, and shutdown the engine. right & right the nr 1 engine iaw mt. nature of condition : over temperature, warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : engine part condition : overheated

suspected fuel leak, left engine. shutdown not required per qrh. 700 left b difference in 30 min. fuel flows : left engine 3.6 ; right engine 3.7. performed engine run of lt engine and inspected for leaks iaw amm 71-00-00. found no evidence of leaks from engine or fuel tanks. aircraft found to be serviceable per service letter 767-sl-28-035-a.

air turn back inflight shutdown declared emergency. loud bang from nr 1 engine. flames reported from exhaust of engine. pilot shutdown nr 1 engine. right & right nr 1 engine per mt. nature of condition : flame fire precautionary procedure : engine shutdown, unsched landing part name : engine part condition : failed

flight 1668 diverted to cae due to a right engine compressor stall on climb out and erratic engine indications. the flight crew declared an emergency and landed without incident. the engine was not shutdown. maintenance found metal in the tai left pipe and the 3rd & 4th stage turbine damage. the engine was replaced.

the flight crew performed air turn back after the nr 1 engine stalled, rolled back, and then did not have any throttle right esponse. the nr 1 engine was shutdown by flight crew. maintenance found turbine damage and the nr 1 engine was replaced.

diversion - to ict for left engine compressor stall at flight level 260. associated rising exhaust gas temperature. engine power reduced to idle, compressor stalls discontinued. engine was not shutdown. flight diverted to ict. borescoped engine found 3rd, 5th and 6 th stage high pressure compressor damage. engine change required.

received no engine valve light when moving the fuel control valve to run on engine start. light work prior to engine start, as well as, after. performed engine fuel shut-off valve actuator test on lt and right engine, iaw b767 amm 28-22-11-801. ops test good.

engine failure nr 1 engine climbing thru 5k. yaw, loud bang rapidly rising exhaust gas temperature. engine exceedance 942 deg. throttle trimmed positioned to idle. engine shutdown. fire bottle discharged. replaced nr 1 engine.

during engine start, number 1 engine would not start. two failed attempts, once on ign left & once ign right. engine spins up normally to 25 % n2, once start lever is advanced minimal exhaust gas temperature increase to about 200 degrees then engine n2 & n1 decelerate s. aborted engine start checklist completed. grounded - yes. debriefed aircrew, verified no circuit circuit-breaker extended, performed #1 engine built in test equipment check with no defects. ref b737-900 fim 80-05 task 806. inspected turbine exhaust for signs of engine failure, no defects noted. performed #1 engine start and start failed, noticed #1 engine fuel spar valve light on. checked circuit-breaker and found it extended. re-set #1 engine spar valve circuit-breaker ref amm 20-60-01-860-801 and per

in cruise at fl 330 we heard a loud bang then engine number 2 failed. after completing engine failure qrh and engine inf light start qrh we were able to restart engine #2. ; no indication of fire or abnormal engine indications. landing weight w as 124.1 [ 01 ] right & right ' d #2 engine per task card ttg8q0064pnj. ops. and leak check good. engine off : cfm56-7b24 ser.
flight 2599 returned to bna due to right engine failure. compressor stall on takeoff. crew shutdown engine per qrh. maintenance found oil in tail pipe and turbine damage. the engine was replaced.

nr 2 engine vibration during climb out, n1 1.5 as power increased, vibration increased. right & right tcc air valve iaw amm 75 - 24. right & right the engine oil filter and checked chip detectors, no metal. performed lpc borescope 6 thru 17 stage. hpt 1 - 3 stage ; low pressure turbine 3rd stage blade inspection iaw amm 72-00. removed, lubricated and reinstalled the nr 2 engine fan blades. right & right helicoils ap 2 and ap 4. replaced the nr 2 engine fan blade set iaw 72-31. performed vibration survey, engine vibration ration remain at permitted levels.

nr 1 engine inbd side under thrust reverser oil is collecting on the thrust reverser, engine filter housing is wet on outside & dripping from bottom. performed a leak checked iaw b767 amm 71-00-00 test 3. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : none part name : housing part condition : leaking

pdis 958 72-00 6611 14sep19 tlh open u log pages : 3112691 during takeoff right engine did not reach full power. left engine 1.6 engine pressure ratio right engine 1.3 engine pressure ratio. after takeoff right engine remained at reduced power until landing. right powe right matched left at settings lower than approximately 1.3 engine pressure ratio. fact 15sep19 00 : 20 tlh replaced #2 engine fuel governor ref mm 73-21 - 01-4-4 leak operation check good.

during routine mx found #1 engine driven pump leaking fuel ( < p > removed and replaced & nbsp ; left engine fuel pump assembly per amm 73 - 11-01401, performed fuel leak check on left engine due to engine fuel pump replacement, ran engine at all power setting iaw 71 - 00-00, no leaks.

the left engine 14th stage manifold assembly separated outboard of the coupling at one of the engine ' s three high pressure bleed ports. this caused a left engine fire indication with the overheat light illuminated in the flight deck during climb after takeoff. the crew performed an in-flight shutdown of the left engine, declared an emergency, and returned to the airport ( cvg ). the airplane was removed from service ( grounded ) and the left engine ' s 14th stage manifold assembly was replaced. also replaced at the left engine were the bonding strap for the pressure regulating valve, the engine fire and overheat detection wiring, and the cooling hose for the throttle push pull cable cooling system. the strap, wiring

aircraft was grounded. right engine thrust reverser light stays on. ac returned to dfw as the right thrust reverser deployed indication light. emergency was declared and the ac returned to dfw. ac landed without incident, landing was not overweight. tighten and cleaned thrust reverser switch on right hand engine operations and leak check good per amm 78-32 - 02.

the crew returned the aircraft to atl after experiencing a compressor stall in the nr 1 engine during climb. the engine was kept running at idle and the qrh was complied with. station cfr saw flames ( in the engine only ) so the flight crew pulled the fire handle for the nr 1 engine. maintenance found turbine damage and metal in tail pipe so the engine was replaced.

engine surge fl350 cruise m.80 min 4 bangs not shutdown operate normal post descent engine nr 1, 15-20 sec. duration, rolled back to 50 %, was experiencing mountain wave, did not spool back-up. throttles were going back and forth. engine 2 : 03 engine 1 : 03 oil service accomplished at den for flight 0309 on 04 mar 14 : 44 : 49 engine 3 : engine 4 : auxiliary power unit : opened nr 1 engine fan and reverser cowls and removed applicable borescope plugs ref amm 72-00-00-200-803-f00. lp 9092875 created against ac 8803 to clear this item from ac.

iffo & diversion - flight crew reported hearing loud rumbles from the left engine and then the engine flamed out. flight crew diverted to stl. maintenance checked left engine chip detector, no defects, borescope inspection per amm 72-00 no demand assigned multiple access ge. removed and replaced number nr 1 engine fuel pump, hydro mechanical unit and electronic engine controllers per amm 73-11 and 73-21. engine operational check ok.

aircraft was in base maintenance : aircraft failed function check flight dur to at takeoff thrust, the right engine stabilized at 98 ) ? n1 and left engine at 90 ) ? n1, as left throttle was advance to match, did not achieve 98 ) ? in climb, both th rottles achieved commanded climb power. both engines achieved climb thrust until engine anti ice applied then the spl it occurred. left ) ( 93 ) ? n1 with right ) ( 97 ) ? n1. advanced left engine and n1 did not achieve commanded n1. replaced hydromechanic al unit ( aala202002169019 ) and fuel pump ( aala202002179016 ) on left hand engine per task card 73-94-121 and amm 73-11-01.

aircraft was in base maintenance : aircraft failed function check flight dur to at takeoff thrust, the right engine stabilized at 98 ) ? n1 and left engine at 90 ) ? n1, as left throttle was advance to match, did not achieve 98 ) ? in climb, both th rottles achieved commanded climb power. both engines achieved climb thrust until engine anti ice applied then the spl it occurred. left ) ( 93 ) ? n1 with right ) ( 97 ) ? n1. advanced left engine and n1 did not achieve commanded n1. replaced hydromechanic al unit ( aala202002169019 ) and fuel pump ( aala202002179016 ) on left hand engine per task card 73-94-121 and amm 73-11-01.
left engine oil pressure was decreasing rapidly. emergency declared & engine shutdown. right & right the nr 1 engine.

air turn back declared emergency, passing 10,000 ' with climb thrust at 95 % n1, the #1 engine started surging between - 5 to - 10 % n1.shortly thereafter #1 n1 rolled back to near idle thrust. engine indications appeared normal. engine bleed air was on and ac packs were in auto. engine anti ice was off. right & right #1 electronic engine control per amm.

aircraft grounded - right engine has slow acceleration in forward thrust. with both thrust levers equal in position, n1 40 percent, takeoff selected for takeoff power, right engine lagged left engine by about 8 percent initially, unequal thrust. at flight level 390, both n1 same, left engine exhaust gas temperature 654 left ( ff ) 2.42, right engine exhaust gas temperature 703 right ( ff ) 2.55. * supplemental right eport : removed and replaced #2 transient bleed valve per amm 75-23-01, operational and leak checks good.

air turn back, declared emergency, inflight shutdown, at 400 above ground level, nr 1 engine indicated zero oil pressure ure, qrh complied with and engine shutdown. right & right the nr 1 engine electronic engine control per amm.

ovheat light after to off during power back on again during thrust increase crew reported engine #1 ovht, engine #1 indications all in the norm range. engine #1 ovht light extinguishes when throttle at idle and lights back-up once throttles advanced performed hpt borescope insp on # 1 engine per amm verified installation of s17 and s11 borescope plugs per 72-00-00-200-807-f00. no defects noted. amm72-00-00-200-807-f00. cw idt gmm requireme next to shoot. performed electronic engine controllers built in test equipment on no 1 engine found no excedences of faults. installed s17 and s11 borescope plugs per ref fim true air speed k 71-06-804. performed pnuematic health check ref maintenance manual found no 1 engine cowl tai valve aft clamp missing and seal ops and left

aircraft returned to platform due to during right engine start, a fuel leak was detected in the right engine. maintenance personnel performed revision, detecting leak fuel by servo fuel heat in the right engine ; so the right engine servo fuel heater was replaced iaw amm task 73-11-07-000400-801-f00 and right engine was run iaw mm 71-00-00, test 3a, tested center orrect

climbing to approximately 436 knots, left engine oil quantity indication began to indicate oil quantity loss. emergency declared, captain started the auxiliary power unit and shutdown the left engine in-flight. the aircraft flew for approximately 20 min utes on single engine and landed safely without further incident. the engine showed no oil leaks. replaced the left engine oil quantity transmitter iaw amm 79-31-01 and accomplished high power engine runs iaw amm 71-00-00, no defects noted.

aircraft was grounded. right engine did not achieve target n1 on takeoff with autothrottle engaged. manually advanced right thrust lever, no additional thrust produced. on climbout past 5000 ft, right engine operated normally and matched lt engine indicating e. replaced right hydromechanical unit and right fuel pump ( aala202012029016 ), iaw amm 73-11-01. operations check good.

after takeoff right engine experienced compressor stalls. right exhaust gas temperature started to fluctuate followed by vibrations and popping sounds. the tower reported flames from right engine. engine was shutdown, emergency declared and flight landed without incident. removed and replaced nr 2 engine iaw alert k179063. nature of condition : flame fire, vibration buffet, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : compressor part condition : stalled

lt engine flame out after touchdown. after landing, using full length on runway into destination station kcvg. flight crew noticed lt engine flamed out shortly after joining sierra taxi way. lt engine oil pressure light illuminated, oil pressure indicated 0 on eicas screen, status message left engine oil pressure. precautionary measures included cut off of lt engine fuel control switch with single engine taxi. aircraft grounded for unscheduled inspection and maintenance. no epcs message. right & right lt engine electronic engine controllers alternator stator control, lt engine electronic engine controllers alternator rotor, lt engine fuel pump, and lt engine fuel control. operational and leak check satisfactory. assurance flight satisfactory. no additional faults noted. aircraft relea

right after takeoff, heard about 5 compressor stalls from the no 3 engine also noticed flashes out of the right window. n1 exhaust gas temperature showed flucuations until power was reduced to climb power takeoff was max thrust engine operated normal remainde right of flight did not shut the engine down no engine parameters exceeded. removed and replaced number 3 engine hydro mechanical unit iaw am m 73-21-01-4-1. requires applicable adjustment test and procedures per amm task 71-00-00-700-809. performed ground il de check, flight idle check and max power assurance check engine run per md11 amm 71-00-00-5-1, all parameters are within left imits. aircraft ok for service.

left engine valve illuminating when ground selected for start for about 45 seconds. left engine started normally after light went out and engine rotation started. cleaned left engine start valve and dry motor left engine twice per amm 71-00-00 operation check good ac ok first officer right service ac remains etops 180.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports on descent, right engine oil pressure went into yellow then red at low thrust power setting. as flight progressed it took higher thrust settings to keep oil pressure out of the caution range. right engine shutdown upon landing. maintenance removed and replaced right hand engine lube and scavenge pump iaw amm 79-21-03. ops test & leak check good.

during descent, received a level 1 engine 3 fadec maintenance message. engine 3 throttle was unresponsive and stuck at 7 % n1. selected fadec alternate mode with no effect. shutdown the nr 3 engine in-flight, uneventful landing. replaced 3 nr 3 engine fan case wiring harnesses for the electronic engine controllers due to throttle resolver wiring shorts, channels a and b. ran engine, throttle response was normal iaw mm 71-02-06, and fim 13n tasks.

aircraft was grounded. right engine did not achieve target n1 on takeoff with autothrottle engaged. manually advanced right thrust lever, no additional thrust produced. on climbout past 5000 ft, right engine operated normally and matched lt engine indicating e. replaced right fuel pump and right hydromechanical unit ( aala202012029014 ), iaw amm 73-11-01. operations check good.

the oil filter bypass alert for nr 2 engine illuminated, reaching fl390. ran qrh, shutdown engine, declared an emergency, and returned to departure. right & right the nr 2 engine iaw mt. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : engine part condition : warning message

inflight shutdown declared emergency, nr 2 engine failed in-flight. right & right nr 2 engine per mt. nature of condition : engine stoppage precautionary procedure : other part name : engine part condition : failed

declared emergency inflight shutdown. during descent into oak, low oil quantity flashing. low oil pressure ensued when engine was at idle. qrh advised engine to be shutdown. right & right engine assembly per mt.

left engine bleed eicas message displayed when left engine anti ice selected. opened thrust reverser on left engine and found two loose wires. tightened wires, ran engine, no messages present at this time. verified built in test equipment on famv, no messages stored iaw b767-300 amm 36-11-16 and amm 71-00-00. good.

air turn back during flight, the number 1 engine stalled with exhaust gas temperature rise, engine was shutdown. aircraft returned safely to departure. maintenance found metal in the tail pipe. maintenance replaced nr 1 engine iaw amm 71-11. engine run and leak checked ok, aircraft returned to service. nature of condition : warning indication, over temperature, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : engine shutdown, unsched landing part name : engine part condition : failed

eicas message left fuel spar valve after engine start engine shutdown after uncommanded exhaust gas temperature rise ( < p > performed operational check of engine shut-off valve, normal on valve on, flight deck indication normal iaw amm 28-22-01. engine idle power run cks norma left 72-00-00 < br > < p > )

returned to departure for engine failure. crew reported at 3800 ' heard a compressor stall and right engine parameters rolled back and exhaust gas temperature climbed. followed the qrh and shutdown the right engine. emergency declared. maintenance found turbine e damage and the right engine was replaced.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports at 1200ft above ground level ( right ) engine thrust reduced to 34 % ( left ) 70 %, ( left ) ff 2000 ( right ) ff 4000, au to throttle disconnected. ( right ) engine control light illuminated ( right ) engine stabilized. ( right ) engine control remained illuminated until shutdown. maintenance removed and replaced right engine left vsv actuator bell crank assembly iaw em 75-00-02. acc omplished idle leak check, actuators test and takeoff power assurance check iaw amm 71-00-003. ops and leak checks good.

at 27,000 ft left engine produced a loud bang and immediately following the engine pressure ratio, n1, n2 rolled back to idle. we conduct ed the engine severe damage qrh and landed with the left engine at idle. the right engine never exceeded any limits during the failure. ref log page 565653 for removed and replaced left engine per workcard 88-7110-9-0010. good. aircraft ok for service.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports upon gate arrival, left engine fuel control switch did not shutdown engine. cycled twice. engine shutdown with t-handle. maintenacne accomplished system operation check iaw amm 71-00-00, found left engine housing assembly pressure valve switch needs to be replaced. removed and replaced left engine housing assembly pressure valve switch iaw amm 73-21-21-15-40, left engine operation check normal and shutdown normal, ok for service.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports during climb out from snu, the #1 n1 was 34 % below on the left engine from the right engine. exhaust gas temperature was 25 less, fuel flow 0.50 less, both bleeds & packs on, isolation valve auto. increasing thrust lever h ad no effect. once in cruise & descent all engine indications were matched up. autothrottle was on throughout except when moving throttle. maintenance troubleshot to engine fuel pump. maintenance removed and replaced fuel pump iaw amm 73-1 1-01. hydro mechanical unit replaced as precautionary. accomlished high power run and leak check ok. ok for servce.

started left engine all normal. started right engine, all normal left engine rolled back, shutdown, visually inspected the nr1 engine inlet and exhaust, interrogated epcs and eicas, no faults or defects noted. performed fim task 73-21-00-815-802-p00, performed fuel pump pressure check 4 on nr 1 engine iaw fim task. removed and replaced nr 1 engine fuel pump filter. iaw mm 73-11-02 performed wiring check on left electronic engine controllers to permanent magnet alternator using fim 73-21 - no fault messages shown. inspected filter and found no debris. 00-815-802-poo step 8. no fault found. performed step 9 open cir the fim fuel pump filter requires leak check per power plant table. cuit check per same fim above without any fault. iaw mm 71-00-00501. right & right relays k nature of condition : engine stoppage precautionary procedure : return to block part name : relay part condition : faulty

aircraft 3603 - inflight shutdown air turn back - returned to atl and declared an emergency due to number 2 engine failure. flight crew performed qrh and shutdown the engine. corrective action : inspection found damage to 8th stage high pressure compressor blades. replaced #2 engine refer to log page 1558574.

right " engine valve " light did not illuminate on shutdown. engine shuts down immediately on selection of " cut off ". cycled indicator light and light test normal. operated switch with engine off, light ops normal. started engine, light operational. performed operation check of the right engine spar valve iaw amm 28-22 - 01. ops checks good. no defects noted.

during takeoff roll, at approximately 120 knots, the right engine engine pressure ratio and n1 began to roll back. system activated. rejected the takeoff. tower reported fire from the right engine. fa ' s reported a loud bang. ops found debris on runway. inspected the right engine and cowling. found a hole at the 12 oclock position of engine acoust aca left section. no cowl damage. the right engine was replaced.

while climbing after takeoff, status messages " left engine oh lp 2 " and " left engine oh lp 2 " displayed and eicas message " left engine oh " displayed. the crew shutdown the left engine and returned to the airport. the airplane was removed from service ( groun dead ended ) and the messages were cleared in accordance with 767 fim 31-41. maintenance personnel found the left engine high pressure pneumatic duct leaking at the duct to engine port flange. the cause of the leak was loose and missing fasteners. the fasteners were installed and tightened.
damage bracket no.4 engine right thrust reverser inner face upper bifurcation forward side.

aircraft was grounded : on takeoff roll, just achieving takeoff thrust, at about 30 knots, eicas messages " engine fail right " and " engine control right " displayed, and there was a loud bang, indicating a possible compressor stall. flight att endants also reported fire ball out the right engine, no fire warnings or indications present. maximum exhaust gas temperature noted was 700 * supplemental report : engine shop reported the suspected root cause of the damage was the material released from the ipc stage 2 vsv inner shroud. the material release from the ipc is not a previously known failure. the investigation results have been reported to rolls royce for further investigation.

air turn back, on takeoff right engine did not achieve to thrust. reduced thrust was 103.5. right engine only achieve 101.1 ( right throttle full forward at ). performed fim 73-21 tree 811 takeoff climb n1 limited by electronic engine controllers. no fault present on electronic engine controllers monitor unit. inspected cdp tubes and mec cdp parts for leaks, no defect noted removed fuel filter, no evidence of debris. replaced fuel filter. visual inspection of vsv cable rigging checks ok per amm 75-34-03. minimum approach & idle n2 check good per amm 71-00-00601. removed and replaced t2 sensor per amm 73-21-05401. ops & leak check pending. accomplished amm 73-21-07 ground idle, amm 71-00-00 test 12 & test 4. operation check normal. ok for service. removed cit sensor per amm 73-21 nature of condition : partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : sensor part condition : faulty

upon starting right engine, engine appeared to start normally but fuel flow stayed at zero. removed and replaced the right engine dual shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11, operation check good.

crew reports engine #2 esn 802765, oil quantity indication 0, oil pressure 19-24. crew shutdown engine. upon insp of #2 engine found oil tank almost empty. metal fragments from starter found in fan cowl. removed starter found frozen. no debris found on mag chip detectors when pulled. replaced starter per amm 80-11-01-400-801-foo leak checked and audio control panel power run, leak checks good and all engine indication normal. accomplished idt inspection of #2 mcd 3ea, o rings and final installation checks good.

climbing thru fl230 a loud bang occured and a drop in power on the left engine was observed. ran qrh 7.6 contacted occ and mcc. ran qrh 7.45 and elected to leave engine running at idle due to normal oil pressure and lack of vibration or further abnormal indications. landed in atl with left engine at idle power. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine.

engine 2 overheat light is on light came on during climbout. light went out and stayed out at reduced power. performed engine auxiliary power unit fire detection control modify built in test equipment procedure found broken wire on upper engine #2 updated with parts info. core fire detection harness and found fault for engine 2 loop a detector fault removed and replaced eng2 fire loop a harness pn m w0326. ref amm 26-11-02. operation check good.

inflight shutdown emergency declared aircraft landed without incident aircraft oos * at 8000 ft left engine failed wno n3 - shutdown left engine ine per qrh. remove and replace ' d left engine per tc5001rr & tc5 002rr.

evidence of bird ingestion on engine #1 inlet cowl at 1230 position ( facing engine ) and outlet guide vane at 1130 position ( < p > completed gvi #1 engine nose cowl and engine intake and found evidence of bird strike at 1230 position on inlet cowl iaw b767 amm 05-51-18. completed visual condition inspection and completed visual inspection engine intake and exhaust area s found no defects iaw b767 amm 72-00-00-206. no evidence of ingestion to the core of the engine noted.

while doing delayed engine start on engine 2 ( 2 start all normal ) noticed engine 3 idling higher than engine 1. all other indications on engine 3 normal ( exhaust gas temperature, ff, etc. decided to shut nr 3 down and restart shutdown nr 3, waited until all indications were zero + 30 seconds. attempted restart on nr 3. all indications normal on initial start shortly after first officer raised the fuel lever at 20 % n2, an aircraft over ground control reported smoke flames coming out of nr 3 engine. complied with tailpipe fire procedures, shut-off fuel lever, motored engine. aircraft behind unsatisfactory still reporting smoke, fired both fire bottles. replaced nr 3 engine.

aircraft not grounded : flight diverted to atl on account of right engine fuel leak. ramp reports fuel dripping from #2 engine drain shroud. emergency was declared. maintenance performed #2 engine actuators test iaw amm 71-71-00, all test passed, no leaks noted.

loud thump and heavy vibration in cruise just at time of day. plz have tech meet unsatisfactory at gate. tomc added additional info from flight crew. after initial report any power setting above 60 % n1 on nr 1 engine produced heavy vibration. engine was kept below that setting and on approach at fl012 the low oil pressure light illuminated and engine shut itself down. due to passenger report of fire both engine auxiliary power unit bottles were discharged. updated sdr selection. see elb low pressure 9130835 for corrective action.

during takeoff, flames were reported out the tail of the left engine. crew aborted takeoff, no fire bottles discharged. borescoped engine no damage found. removed and replaced number one engine hydro mechanical unit iaw amm 73-21. leak and operation check ok, aircraft returned to service. nature of condition : flame fire precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : engine part condition : fire

approximentely 30 minutes in to flight ( fl350 ) crew heard a very loud bang with significant aircraft yaw. observed engine ine no 1 n1 roll back with confirm engine out on fms. determined n1 on engine 1 had seized and exec uded phase 1. complied and completed enging 1 fire or severe damage check list. recovered at kden runway 35l. replaced left engine.

nr 1 engine failed at 3500 ft message on approach in rain with nacelle anti ice on engine restarted automatically. followed fim 71-0 0 figure 114 for auto shutdown event. also followed powerplant engineering guidance to accomplish borescope inspection for internal damage. checked nr 1 engines turbine exhaust and inlet area, no trouble found per fim 71-00 fig 114. accomplished inspections of chip detectors, supply and scavenge filters. no defects noted. performed nr 1 engine high pressure compressor 1st-6th b si inpection and chked ok by stk per amm 72-00-00. performed engine idle run and part power run successfully. aircraft returned to service.

left engine quanity in cruise showed 0 percent with oil pres fluctuati ons from low 20s to 40s found #1 engine oil level at 88 % on flight deck indication and amm 12-13-11. verified oil was within sight glass on tank, serviced to full iaw entering turbulence and returned to normal on approach after flaps set to 15. crew reported on debrief, indication issues started after ref lp 4510990 and 4513248 for corrective action replaced #1 engine lube pump and accomplished oil system flush

smell of engine oil during engine start taxi, climb, and descent. conducted inspection of oil leaks on all 4 engines. ran all 4 engines individually with all 3 packs on, no odors observed in flight deck, crew rest, galley or main deck noted during engine run, iaw amm 71-10-00.

left engine would not shutdown when fuel cutoff moved to cutoff. it ran for approximately 25 seconds before shutting down. removed left engine fuel flow governor as per amm 73-21-01-4-4. installed left engine ffg iaw amm 73-21-01-4-4. per formed engine leak check test 1 and idle check. leak checked ok. all parameters witihin the limit. remain high power test 9, 10 and 11. ran engine nr 1 and 2 iaw jrh, and performed tests 9, 10, and 11 iaw mm 71-00-00-5-3-r, all parameters normal, aircraft ok for service.

after engine start, the left duct pressure indicates 7 pounds per square inch with engine power at idle, aircraft packs in auto and engine anti ice off. grounded - yes. found muscle air line to nr 1 engine high stage valve broken. replaced line and leak check ok. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : none part name : tube part condition : broken

surge or stall of engine during forward thrust, left engine accomplished iaw fim 71-05-00-810-819-n00, right & right the left pressure shutoff valve iaw amm 36-11-09-400-801-001, and 36-10-00-700-804. all functional checked normal. accomplished a lt engine actuator test. functional checked ok with high power engine run. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : shut-off valve part condition : faulty

ship 6823 - the flight crew performed an air turn back after a suspected engine compressor stall during takeoff. all par ammeter returned to normal, but the qrh required a turn back due to over water operation. corrective action : maintenance inspected both engines per the fim and no discrepancies were identified by the borescope of the left and right engines. the fuel control unit and fuel pump were replaced on the #2 engine. the aircraft has returned to service. reaching fl390, after level off, left engine experienced two separate thrust reductions with accompanying aircraft vibrations. after each separate reduction & vibration, the engine recovered normal ops. no limit exceeded and mc notified. removed and replaced the fuel control and performed engine run, no leaks and operation check normal iaw amm 73-21. replaced electronic engine controllers pt2tt2 probe iaw amm 73-21. and performed high power run, operation check normal. nature of condition : vibration buffet, warning indication, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : other part name : fuel control part condition : malfunctioned

open u during climb dept kord approximately 5000 loud banging noise followed by yaw, autopilot engaged, leading edge n1 30 %, fuel flow approximately. 4000pph, right engine normal, lt engine back to normal. second occurrence banging low n1 & ff on lt engine eicas " left engine high pressure shut off valve " ( so unded like compressor stall ) tat 14 deg. ran qrh, engine high pressure shut off valve checklist, no other occurrence. returned to ord. performed borescope insp per 767 mm 72-00-00-6 for stall, no defects noted. hydro mechanical unit req right & right per tsi wri 72-002710. removed hydro mechanical unit iaw mm 73-21-14-4, circuit-breaker d25 on p11 and e1 on p6, pulled and collared. removal completed plates for hard lines must be removed from new other fasteners and hardware if req. cont right & i per amm 73-21-14-4 thru installation step 3, e, ( 8 ). du

nr 1 engine stayed in reverse after landing, tried cycling, no help, associated idle disagree eicas message. replaced the brake lock, nr 1 engine inbound thrust reverser. found right middle flexible shaft upper end, twisted off and replaced.

in-flight shutdown and an air turn back with a left engine oil issue. crew reported left oil temperature climbed to 180 degrees and iaw qrh shutdown the engine. maintenance found the left engine oil temperature bulb connector loose. the oil temperature rise was able to be duplicated by shaking the connector wires. the connector was replaced and pins replaced. an engine run was performed and the aircraft was returned to service.

enroute from kafw to kjfk left engine shutdown and left engine fuel valve eicas message displayed. at fl210 ( climbout ) exhaust gas temperature exceeded at 831, left thrust reverser was reduced with left engine fuel valve light on. crew complied with qrh procedures. air turn back to destination station kafw with emergency declaration. landing uneventful with no additional precautionary actions. aircraft grounded for unscheduled maintenance. work in progress.

nr 1 engine surged. flight attendants and passengers report flames coming out of the exhaust. aircraft shook several times. engine lost power. flight crew set engine to idle and surge stopped, landed with one engine. the aircraft was gro unded.

on landing, a mechanic reported sparks coming from left engine on reverse thrust and when back into positive thrust coming off runway. all engine indications were normal. inspected inlet and exhaust. no damage noted. no fadec faults reported.

right engine failed at approximately 7000 ' msl during descent. initially noted right generator off, then utility busses, autothrottles, and autopilot. engine was a slow shutdown. right oil pressure was zero. windmilled right engine for 7 - 8 minutes. no vibration or noise was noted. landed uneventful. removed the right engine fuel drains, tank ejector valve, filter and inspected. no debris noted. cleaned filter and reinstalled iaw amm 71-71-04-2. removed the right engine lp filter element and inspected. no debris noted. installed new filter element iaw mm 73-11-10-4. troubleshot iaw fim 71-05 ft 807. removed hp fuel pump verified shaft not sheared. verified voltages at ffg connector. iaw fim block 24, re nature of condition : engine flame out precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : governor part condition : malfunctioned

reported that left engine has low oil during flight. serviced engine oil 3 qts iaw amm 12-13-01 inspected left engine iaw amm 71-05-03. no defects noted. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : other part name : oil system part condition : low quantity

on takeoff power up, the right engine bleed discrete light illuminated. the left & right engine bleed eicas & master caution lights illuminated and there was a smell of something burning. the takeoff was aborted at a speed of less than 60 knots. the airplane was removed from service ( grounded ) and a takeoff power engine run was performed on the right engine. no faults or messages were displayed. there was not a burning smell during the engine run. the defective right engine high pressure controller was replaced. the cause of the burning smell is unknown.

aircraft in base maintenance - emergency declared - during functional check flight, #2 engine inflight shutdown and reli ght test, failed to restart. no fuel flow observed, all other engine indications normal. no engine valve light observed when fuel control switch moved to run. removed and replaced right engine fuel flow governor per amm 73-94-01, operationa left check good. [ see associated report aala2020029005 ]
left engine spar light valve very slow to extinguish in start or shutdown. removed and replaced the left engine fuel shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. operation check ok.

during climb, received oil filter bypass light for the nr 2 engine 2. ran qrh and light did not extinguish. inflight shutdown, air turn back, declared an emergency. right & right the nr 2 engine iaw mt. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : warning light part condition : illuminated

pdis 915 76-15 1679 17oct19 cdg open u log pages : 2941127 at the gate, left engine would not shutdown using the fuel control switch. the spar valve was moving but the engine valve light would illuminate when the fc sw was placed off. finally pulled fire handle. checked left engine fire sw s37 and found 139 ohms between pin 7 and 19. removed and replaced left engine fire handle as per amm 26-21-02-4.performed left engine fire switch inspection check iaw amm 26 - 21-03-6, all check satisfactory.

pilot reported a left engine high pressure shut off valve message and bleed light illuminated during takeoff roll, regained pressure with thrust lever retarded. icing conditions present entire time. duct pressure 33 pounds per square inch. the aircraft was grounded. maintenance found the high pressure shut off valve defective and stuck in the open position. removed and replaced left engine high pressure shut off valve iaw amm 36-11-07. accomplished operational test of bleed air system iaw amm 36-11-00 and engine ground test iaw amm 71-00-00-715-066. good.

nr 1 engine oil filter bypassed. diverted, and declared an emergency. found accessary gear-box electronic engine control alternator shaft sheared. right & right the 1 engine iaw mt. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : shaft part condition : sheared

ship 6819 - the flight crew diverted the aircraft to slc following the #1 engine rolling back to 25 % n2 and no throttle response. engine was subsequently shutdown by flight crew per the qrh during descent. corrective action : maintenance first officer und numerous epcs messages and replaced the electronic engine controllers alternator stator and the electronic engine controllers. an intermittent open wire was also located so the harness was replaced.

left engine shutdown in-flight due to a vibration. accomplished fim 71-05 ft 814, no metal particles found in the inle tor exhaust areas, no comtamination found on the master chip detector. accomplished lt engine borescope inspection ofthe lpc, high pressure compressor, hpt blades, combustor and fuel nozzles iaw 72-00-00 and fim 71-05 - tree 814. no defects noted. during troubleshooting iaw fim 71-05 tree 814, found the left engine right pylon connector d4223p contaminated with hydraulic fluid. cleaned area and removed & replaced the connector iaw swpm 20-63-00, 20-10-04, wd 2233-11, 71-s1-11, 73-34-11, 75-32-12, and 77-31-11. continuity and insulation checked ok. accompliashed a lt engine vibration survey test iaw amm 71 - nature of condition : vibration buffet precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : connector part condition : contaminated

right engine fire light bells passing approximately. 800 ft on takeoff. no engine indications of fire or damage. fire light went out before blowing fire bottle or shutdown engine. landed with right engine at idle per qrh. found anti ice duct blown. no damage to case or cowls. removed and replaced duct and cowl anti ice valve per amm 75-10. ops and leak checked good. ok for service.

passing through 8-9000 feet noticed exhaust gas temperature gauge turn yellow showing 806 degrees and n1 gauge at 101 % on left engine. left engine running much higher engine pressure ratio than right engine. decided to air turn back to cdg. at lower power settings, left engine ran be tter matching the right engine. landed with no further issues. pictures of debris found attached picture of engine display taken by pilot in-flight where we see higher ff, n1, exhaust gas temperature and a low engine pressure ratio p1 probe inspection check performed iaw amm 73-21-04-6 and found debris stuck inside. disconnected p1 air tubes at p1 air accumulator and at ffg and purged system with dry nitrogen. p1 probe is now clear and good air-flow at all points. reconnected air tubes iaw amm 70-51-0

during routine engine shop visit, the 2-5 spool from engine was found with a stg 1 seal teeth missing fragment. the engine was removed for scheduled high time engine removal for full performance restoration sv. decided to launch an hardware investigation to identify the root cause of such missing fragment occurrence.

crew reported the aircraft experienced left engine roll back and returning to sti. corrective action : no inlet or exhaust damage, performed actuators test with no faults. chip detectors checked clean, replaced hydro mechanical unit and engine fuel pump. engine run checks good.

engine valve closed light did not illuminate bright blue from dim when start lever was raised to idle ; instead light immediately extinguished. grounded - yes. removed and replaced #1 engine hydro mechanical unit ref asa tc n8473000 & 1. idle power leak check, good. no leak noted. actuator test, good. no fault on electronic engine controllers built in test equipment cks engine valve closed lt, operated normal.

inspection type : na on taxi in to phl, left engine failed. left engine valve light on. left engine lp pump illuminated. ts per fim 71-05-00 and 75-90-03, 73-21-815. all inspection ckd good. cleared message. performed engine run with packs, generator switching. all ckd good. problem happened on power swap per inbd crew. cleaned electronic engine controllers & tpu connectors, engine run ckd good.
right engine spar valve did not cycle during start. right & right engine fuel shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. operation check good.

right engine spar valve failed to illuminate upon engine start. performed ops checks of engine spar valve iaw 28-22-11 and ran engine at idle iaw amm 71-00-00. operation check normal at this time. inbd flight crew also reported ops checks normal. this cl ears mddr. dispatch jl0319z.

on-board flight crew reported right engine fire lp 2 status message during nr 2 engine start. message cleared shortly after. rem oved and replaced nr 2 engine loop 2 control fire overheat card, precautionary operational check of engine auxiliary power unit cargo fire overheat tested good no defects noted per amm 26-11-03 - 012-001.

aircraft was not grounded. when throttles advanced for takeoff nr 2 engine spool up lagged behind nr 1 resulting in asymmetrical thrust. takeoff aborted. flight crew accomplished engine run up with all indications normal. subsequent takeoff was uneventful. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : engine part condition : slow

diversion declared emergency, on takeoff nr 2 engine was 3 to 5 sec slower to takeoff thrust than nr 1 while at cruise f l290, 320 knots indicated air speed began feeling a full aircraft vibration, fa ' s called with reports of flames out nr 2 engine, nr 2 engine n1 was rolled back to 35 to 40 %. right & right hydro mechanical unit iaw mt.

discovered fuel leak from nr 1 engine while airborne. found fuel leaking from left engine low pressure fuel filter. heli coil had backed out of filter housing and o-ring deformed and leaked. right & i left engine low pressure fuel filter housing per amm 73-11-01. right & i fuel filter per amm 73-11-01. performed engine run and leak check per amm 71-00-11 710-801 test 2a. no further leaks. ok for service.

on post flight walk-around found fuel leak right engine. on right engine retorqued & " fuel in " tube on intergrated drive generator fuel oil heat exchange anger, iaw 24-11-10. ran engine, per 71-00-00, leak ck good.

strong oil odor throughout cabin and cockpit after engine start with bleeds configured. found the 2 engine ip compressor stage 2 and stage 3 oil stain on engine blades. replaced the nr 2 engine iaw amm 71-00-02. nature of condition : smoke fumes odors sparks, fluid loss precautionary procedure : return to block part name : engine part condition : leaking
on approach to dtw at approximately 2000 ' above ground level, right engine experienced compressor stall. stall stopped when throttle was retarded. emergency declared. right engine replaced.

pdis 108 73-35 4592 13feb19 can open u log pages : 2612304 left engine fuel filter eicas message came on during climb. eicas message came on and off several times and remained on throughout. most off the flight. left engine vibrator ated and vibration increased during descent couplied with non-normal and normal checklists declared an emergency and right eturned to can. per fim 73-11-00-1, removed left engine fuel filter element per amm 73-11-02-6, filter element checked normal, no contamination. replaced fuel filter differential pressure switch. engine ran as per jrh, all parameters norm al.

discrepancy : during climb nr 2 engine exhaust gas temperature light illuminated autothrottle disconnect manual thrust reduction. large thrust lever split for equal thrust. autopilot & at instrument landing system engine performance normal. corrective action : performed visual check of inlet and exhaust, no defects noted. checked vsv actuator rig vbv cable rig. replaced start valve for not seating closed & had pneumatic leak. operations checked good. performed power run to 80 percent n1, no defects noted.

flight diverted due to a low fuel flow on the right engine. uneventful landing. removed and replaced the nr 2 engine electronic engine controllers iaw amm 73-21-07 and engine pressure ratio transmitter iaw amm 77-11-01. operational checked good. aircraft was grounded. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : transmitter part condition : faulty

aircraft returned to platform due to during engine start, the left engine fuel filter by pass light turned on. maintenance personnel replaced the left engine differential pressure switch and fuel filter iaw amm 73-34-01, tested correct. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : pressure switch part condition : failed

aircraft was grounded : diverted to dfw account left engine fuel filter bypass illuminated on, climbout. all engine indications normal. light went, off on twice in-flight. removed and replaced #1 engine fuel filter per 73-11-02, run and leak check accomplished as required, no leaks noted.

aircraft was grounded. emergency declared. mia scl flight returned to mia account right engine throttle uncommanded roll back. overweight landing uneventful. removed and replaced right engine thrust lever angle resolver per amm 76-11-02 ( aala20171106002 ), right engine electronic controller per amm 73-21-11 ( aala201711139020 ), and right electronic engine controllers loom assembly per amm 71-50-00. operational checks good. nature of condition : partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : wire harness part condition : faulty

after engine start left engine was idling higher than right engine, item was crew deferrable. the deferral required more fuel to be added for flight. aircraft back to blocks, grounded by maintenance until deferral was complete and fuel was added.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports left engine thrust lever linkage binding. not auto thrust. auto thrust normal. main tenance accomplished fim task 76-11-00 fig 105a. accomplished thrust lever load test iaw amm 76-11-00-501. no problems found at this time. no binding noted.

left engine valve light illum during engine start no fuel flow. replaced fuel pump ref amm 73-11-01. accomplished acceleration time test ref jrh 2-5-64. time test passed. fuel flow was normal at idle ( 1.09 ), flight idle ( 1.49 ) and 95 % to ( 1.39 engine pressure ratio fuel flow at 13.6k ). other engine parameters were normal. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : pump part condition : faulty

air turn back due to a right engine problem. at 9000 feet, crew heard a compressor stall and observed right exhaust gas temperature flashing. the throttles were set back to idle for rest of flight. an emergency was declared. maintenance found turbine damage and replaced the right engine.

diverted, emergency declared, right engine oil filter eicas. ran qrh shutdown engine. accomplished alert inspection iaw power plant engineering iaw mm 79-21-05, and 79-35-01. flushed system & changed filters two times, serviced oil, replaced oil pressure delta p switch ground run operation check normal, leak checked good.

lt engine compressor stall ( moderate ) all engine indications normal in climb through 35000 '. flight crew elected to divert to cvg. aircraft was grounded by maintenance. maintenance found vsv cable binding. engine was borescoped and no damage found. aircraft returned to service

aircraft was grounded : on takeoff roll, left engine n1 lagged well behind right engine. during initial climb left engine indicating e exhaust gas temperature overtemp to 979. * supplemental report : accomplished vsv vbv rig check per amm 75-31-00 75-31-02. accomplished engine compressor wash per task card 71-97-05. accomplished borescope inspection per task 71-96-01. no findings noted. acc omplished power assurance test per amm 71-00-00. all parameters of test within amm limits. ok for service.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports right engine filter bypass light illuminated after takeoff, turns on and off intermittently. maintenance accomplished fim 73-05-00-810-f00, no faults noted. iaw fim, replaced #2 engine fuel filter iaw j outboard card 73-94-13 and replaced fuel filter differential switch iaw amm 73-34-01. ran engine, operation check good. ok for service.

the flight was diverted to msp following the loss of oil from the #1 engine. an emergency was not declared, the engine w as not shutdown, and the aircraft landed uneventfully. corrective action : maintenance visually inspected the engine but did not find any external oil leaks. no oil was found in the tailpipe. the deoiler ejector port seal, rotating seal & packing, and starter carbon seal were replaced per amm 72-61-02.

during takeoff right engine rolled back to sub idle. the takeoff was aborted at 70 knots. right & right the nr 2 engine fuel control, fuel pump, and electronic engine controllers. removed and reinstalled the original pt2tt2 probe iaw amm 73-21. mtc found fuel flow transmitter housing separated causing a large leak upstream of the fuel distribution valve. the transmitter was replaced. per formed test 3, 3a, 6, 7, and test 15. engine leak and operation check good.

air turn back - during climb out the left engine vibration was indicating 4.3. crew complied with qrh and aircraft returned to jfk. corrective action : maintenance replaced airborne vibration monitor and number one engine fan blades per b737 amm. all vibes normal on high power run, aircraft returned to service.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports on initial power application for takeoff, the number one engine was substantally s lower to spool up than the #1 engine. maintenance removed and replaced the #1 engine main engine control iaw job card 12 l40073001 and leak check was good iaw jobcard 12l40072003.

start on nr 2 engine, n2 indicating 26 % when start lever brought up to idle. no fuel flow or ignition indication. followed aborted start iaw qrh. aircraft grounded. performed nr 2 engine start twice. engine start normal, no abnormal parameters. normal nr 2 engine start using auxiliary power unit, no faults noted. all iaw amm 71-00-00-800-810-f00. visual impeller rotation inspection iaw amm 73-11-01-200-801, found no rotation. inspected lubrication flow screen, no contamination. replaced fuel filter iaw amm 73-11-02. replaced the fuel pump, hydro mechanical unit, fuel heater servo, and heat exchanger iaw ea 800-71ea-18794. ran engine by start 2 times, normal starts. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : other part name : unknown part condition : malfunctioned

pdis 359 76-10 6450 14feb20 ont open u log pages : 3200450 during descent number 2 throttle would not decrea se below approximately 71 % n1. during attempted throttle movements in auto and manual throttle number 2 throttle would advance on it ' s own. due to this we decided to shutdown number 2 engine iaw the engine shutdown inflight, qrh check list. we declared an emergency with ontario approach control. fact 14feb20 12 : 27 ont complied with ea 8-7600-t0352444, clean and purge engine #2 throttle cable, ref amm 76-11-01-2. ops checks good. complied with amm 72-00-00-6

left engine flame out ( shutdown ) occurred while descending through approximately 10,000 feet. the quick reference handbook  s engine failure and engine in-flight start check list was completed. the engine restart was successful. the airplane was removed from service ( grounded ) and a bolt was found missing at the aft side of the left engine  s servo fuel heater, causing a fuel leak. the servo fuel heater  s gasket seal was replaced and the missing bolt was installed. the cause for the in-flight shutdown was a missing bolt in the servo fuel heater. nature of condition : fluid loss, engine flame out precautionary procedure : other part name : bolt part condition : missing

ship 5650 - air turn back inflight shutdown - during climb out at approximately 17,000ft the left engine throttle became unresponsive. crew performed air turn back to msp. flight crew shutdown the engine per qrh. corrective action : electronic engine controllers and fcu replaced, wiring che cks performed. found pitot static tlr fb int message during check outs. verified short internal to thrust lever resolver. resolver replaced and messages cleared. system checks good. aircraft returned to service.

aircraft grounded, during descent, experienced a sudden loss of pressurization, all masks deployed at fl 380 cabin alt light came on and alt horn sounding, both bleed trip off lights illuminated. crew followed bleed trip off in qrh & pressurization re-stored. engine anti ice was on. an emergency was declared, and landed safely without further incident. acc omplished health checks for lt engine iaw wc 4414, & right engine iaw wc 4415. replaced lt engine bleed air regulator, lt engine 390 degree precooler control valve sensor, lt engine 450 degree, bleed air overtemp sensor, right engine 390 degree, precooler control valve sensor, & right engine 450 degree, bleed air overtemp sensor.

status message " left engine prv " ( < p > performed fim 36-10 ft 878, found wire on the prv to be touching safety wire. adjusted wire and re secured. had flight crew perform left engine idle run. no status message after shutdown. good at this time. engine run iaw amm 71-00-00.

1. right engine failure during cruise, followed qrh procedures and diverted to bro, declaired emergency uneventful landing. 2. during walk-around, discovered passenger cabin window at row 11 right was damaged. 1. during ts found #2 engine had considerable foreign object debris damage. remove and replace # 2 engine iaw wo #4863, tc 71-900-01-01. performed adjustment test engine ground run up engine change iaw tc 71-900-02-01. items s, a, b, + center, synchronization system test 6, electrical system check + item, engine generator field disconnect + operational check could not be accomplished due to right generator failure to come on-line. adjusted part power trim and engine low idle trim iaw md80 amm 71-00-00. all parameters within limits. cw boeing tc 76-021-01-02, e

left engine thrust lever froze in-flight at aproxim tely 1.5 engine pressure ratio, while passing 30,000 ft, turned autothrottles off and made no difference. able to break loose with a subsequent bind, broke free again and was ok the remainder of the flight. performed an inspection and check of fuel flow governor, the input lever torque is within limits iaw amm 73-21-01 - 6. checked lower, intermediate and upper control box assemblies iaw amm 76-11-10-6, no defects found. performed a throttle push pull check iaw 76-11-00-5, found to be within limits. performed an autothrottle test iaw 22-10-00-5, no faults. performed a nr 1 engine idle run, operation check normal. throttle moves free with no binding.

during takeoff roll, the right engine bleed off eicas and off light illuminated zero duct pressure indicated. complied with fim 36-20 ft 104. right engine pressure shutoff valve fault, inspected right engine pressure shutoff valve valve, sense lines, and electrical connector, built in test equipment checked the air supply, no faults, performed ground run of right engine, pneumatics operation check good iaw amm 71-00-00. nature of condition : false warning precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : warning light part condition : false activation

aircraft was grounded. flight diverted to dfw due to loss of oil qty in right engine. troubleshooting revealed an interna left leak in high pressure compressor section, engine change declared. supplemental report : replaced right engine, iaw workcard 71-49-01. operations check good. ( closed )

upon descent into destination approxmately fl 180 in imc rain right engine fire warning and light came on. ran phase ones and qrh for right engine fire. upon right engine shutdown, fire light went out then came back on so followed qrh and fired the fire bottle. red light and warning then went out and stayed out. emergency landed, fire crew, then mx, declared no obse rvable fire completed right engine fire and overheat detection system operation check ref b 757 amm 26-1 1-00-5 checked normal at this time. see wri updates for addtional work pref rorm ed and parts changed see wri 26208278 for #2 engine fire bottle change. conf call with mocc

aircraft was grounded. emergency declared. mia scl flight returned to mia account right engine throttle uncommanded roll back. overweight landing uneventful. removed and replaced right engine thrust lever angle resolver per amm 76-11-02, right engine electronic controller per amm 73-21-11 ( aala201711139020 ), and right electronic engine controllers loom assembly per amm 71-50-00 ( aala201711139021 ). operational checks good. descending through 9000 ' left vibration went up to at least 4.9 with flashing box. autothrottle disconnected. engines at or close to id leading edge. vibration dropped to 3.9 then power was brought up and normal for remainder of flight. grounded - yes. flight leg 6 of flight history recorded no. 1 engine fan vibration 4.95, high pressure compressor. low pressure turbine vibration. for #1 engine accomplished steps e. step e. replaced mw0313 harness installation tests pass ref b737-800 amm 71-51-03-400-801-f00. accomplished repair confirmation of fim 77-31 task 806 built in test equipment test

aborted right engine start iaw qrh. not enough bleed pressure. accomplished operational check of engine ( right ) duct pressure 25 pounds per square inch, n2 fuel, flow 0.7 at engine start. no discrepancies noted operation check good iaw amm 71-00-00.

upon climb - passing through 8500 feet. the fire warning for the right engine fire warning illuminated and the fire bell was going off. engine was shutdown and feather and returned to base. upon inspection of the engine, it was determined to be an indication issue with no evidence of fire being found. aircraft is still being inspected to determine the root cause of the indication.

inflight shutdown declared emergency, in idle during arrival descent, number 2 engine quit running.. assembly is trailing edge down restart was attempted iaw qrh, but was not successful. right & right fuel nozzle filter on #2 engine iaw amm.

aircraft returned to platform due to during left engine start, a fuel leak was detected. detected fuel leak in the transient bleed valve drain. the left engine was motoring, after it was started and engine operational test was performed iaw amm 71-71-00, no confirming fuel leak, all correct. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : other part name : unknown part condition : leaking

left engine has a small fuel seepage from the hpt turbine cooling valve shroud drain. removed and replaced left engine tcc valve iaw amm 75-24-01, test ran the nr 1 engine for leak check, no leaks found, operation check good. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : other part name : valve part condition : leaking

during taxi flames were reported to be emanating from the nr 2 engine tailpipe. the engine was shutdown. emergency was declared. performed step 6 & 7 from ntsb. performed gvi of nr 2 engine and surrounding area for evidence of fire damage. found no evidence of fire or damage to the nr 2 engine. flight data recorder, cvr, and slides were removed and fdau was uploaded to pcmia card. nature of condition : flame fire precautionary procedure : other part name : engine part condition : fire

on initial walk-around found fuel leak on left engine, fuel servo heater assembly. removed and replaced left engine servo fuel heater iaw amm 73-11-09. leak check good. performed engine run per amm 71-00-00. found no further defects.

left engine oil quantity low. aircraft diverted to ksfo when reading 5 qts. during engine motoring, found oil tubing leaking at lower case. borescope found excessive oil leakage upper quadrant with damage to oil line. engine change under way. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : line part condition : leaking

left engine popping noise reported by tower and other aircraft. inspected both engine inlets and outlets, master chip detectors and mcd ' s iaw amm 79-21 - no trouble found. downloaded pcmcia card but card unable to load, right & right pcmcia card iaw amm 31-36. found epcs message for nr 1 engine, s-pdiu, s-274-18, s-275-15 and s-354-29 iaw fim 77-35 fim 71-01. replaced electronic engine controllers al tte rnator stator and electronic engine controllers iaw amm 73-21. ops tested ok. right & right the 14th stage bleed valve iaw amm 75-32. right & right nr 1 engine indicating e alternator oil seals iaw amm 72-61. installed the stator iaw amm 73-21. performed high power run and no leaks noted.

#2 engine fuel pressure switch is leaking from forward fitting located above fuel filter. removed and replaced #2 engine fue left pressure switch packing, and re installed #2 engine fuel pressure switch iaw amm 73-34-01. pending leak check. performed leak check iaw amm 71-00-00, no leaks noted.

inspection type : na air turn back inflight shutdown. emergency declared, aircraft landed wout incident. left engine loss on rotation, bird strike, multiple birds. left engine shutdown inflight. cw birdstrike inspection, iaw amm 05-51-18-212-001, ref logbook 590 403 3 for right & right of nr 1 engine.
left engine valve indication inop. removed and replaced left engine fuel shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. good at this time.

eicas message for fuel pump, right engine shutdown. removed and replaced the fuel control unit on the right engine iaw amm 7 3-21-01, operation check good. leak checked good nature of condition : warning indication, engine stoppage precautionary procedure : return to block part name : fcu part condition : malfunctioned
during descent autothrottle commanded from idle to enroute power setting. emergency declared. nr 2 engine failed to accelerate. right & right the nr 2 engine iaw mt.
