aircraft was grounded. left engine fuel control would not shutdown engine. removed and replaced left engine fuel control switch iaw amm 76-11-02 and swpm 20-61-11. operational check good. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : none part name : switch part condition : faulty

at 38,000, ft oil quantity on the nr 1 engine dropped to zero, oil pressure was in and out. when pressure decreased to red line, crew shutdown the engine and flew on one engine for 20 minutes until arrival. maintenance accomplished magnetic chip detector iaw amm 79-21-05. inspected engine after in-flight. windmilling iaw amm 71-00-00. found starter seal leaking and replaced lt engine starter seal iaw amm 80-11-01. accomplished satisfactory operational check. aircraft was grounded. nature of condition : fluid loss, warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : seal part condition : leaking

right engine fuel filter eicas message illuminated intermittently throughout flight. remained for last 2 hours of flig heat. replaced the fuel filter, found debris on the filter element iaw amm 73-11-08. accomplished a nr 2 engine run up t estimate, nr 3, ops & leak checked good iaw amm 21-00-00. no eicas mgs displayed during the engine run up. ok for service.

aircraft returned to platform due to during taxing, a fuel leak was detected in the left engine. maintenance personnel performed revision, detecting the fuel servo heater with fuel leak. so the left engine fuel servo heater was replaced, iaw amm 73-11-07 and left engine was run iaw mm 71-00-00, test 3a, tested correct.

during engine start, the right engine exhaust gas temperature reached 668 degrees using rich. aborted the engine start. followed qrh. performed visual inspection of lp turbine and the internal part of the exhaust collector iaw amm 78-11-04601 and no damage found. aircraft ok for service. nature of condition : warning indication, over temperature precautionary procedure : return to block part name : engine part condition : overtemp

nr 2 engine would not develop climb thrust out of 10,000 feet, returned to departure. right & right the nr 2 engine fuel pump iaw mt. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : pump part condition : faulty
during inspection, found a cracked bracket on forward bulkhead at the right upper engine thrust reverser. the bracket was replaced.

diverted, due to the right engine oil quantity indicated 7 quarts and was decreasing. maintenance found the right engine indicating e starter leaking at gearbox split line. replaced the starter packings and complied with high power run, no leaks noted. aircraft returned to service.

passengers reported flames sparks in rear right engine and a popping noise on takeoff. no reported smoke in cabin. no abnormal engine indication. no overheat or fire indication in cockpit. bwi fire ; rescue reported normal engine temperatu res both front and rear of engine. [ 01 ] performed mtsi ttg8q005lltr for inspecting the inlet exaust chip detectors and sumps for damage or any abnormalities no defects noted also performed engine borescope no defects noted ref log page 17 70380 also performed engine power run per amm 71-00-00 ops ck good

during taxi out, the right engine shutdown by itself after being stabilized at idle. another aircraft reported small tail pipe fire after the engine had shutdown. replaced the right fcu, inspected inlet and exhaust. system operation is normal. as follow-up, found the burner pressure flex line damaged near the electronic engine controllers. removed and replaced the burner pressure flex line, checks good. nature of condition : flame fire precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : line part condition : damaged

returned to departure after a climb out engine vibration 1.1 nr 1 engine cowl valve light ( open ) began flashing. at fl 300 with switch off cowl valve light came on bright blue engine vibration 0.6. during climbout, began feeling medium frequency airframe vibration throughout aircraft, primarily located in floor aft of overwing exits gear and flap position h ad no effect, increased during approach. no emergency declared, landed without incident. replaced the nr 1 engine cowl tai valve iaw amm 30-21-11. ops and leak checked good.

discrepancy : crew reported that after departure from klrd and climbing through 10000 feet, the nr 3 engine failed with associated vibrations. they declared an emergency and performed the engine fire, severe damage or separation checklist and landed at the departure airport without further incident. corrective action : usa jet maintenance in klrd inspected the engine and found all four stages of the turbine section to have foreign object debris. they removed and replaced the nr 3 engine, iaw usa jet gmm volume 4 chapter 72.01.1 to 72.01.26. all operations and leaks normal during engine trim run.

at fl 320, after 1 hr 25 min of flight, we heard a loud bang. #2 engine rolled back and shutdown. auto start tried several times to re light but it did not start. n1 21 %, n2 22 %, oil pres 9. highest exhaust gas temperature during restart was 825. descended to fl 300 and accomplished qrh. since engine wasn ' t seized, attempted another start. did not start, engine was cutoff. removed and replaced #2 engine assembly per atlas air task card b-72-099-00-01. accomplished mcs package 52306 as assigned.

diverted due to approximately one hour into flight, the left engine oil quantity dropped to zero. oil pressure also dropped. crew consulted qrh, and contacted dispatch and mc and decision was made to divert to ams. emergency was declared when request to dump fuel was made. arff reported a brake fire and followed the aircraft to the gate. right inboard rear fuse plug melted. engine was pulled back to idle. aircraft landed with left engine on with 9 pounds per square inch oil pressure. mtc found oil streaking from recoup ducts in tailpipe. corrective action : engine change. ( 9638068 ) nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : engine part condition : leaking

system a hydraulic quantity indication. an emergency was declared, and landed without further incident. system a engine driven pump illuminated for duration of flight, greater than 5 minutes. the aircraft was grounded. replaced left engine hydraulic pump iaw amm 29-11-11. replaced all pressure, return, engine and emdp filter case. replaced emp iaw amm 29-11-21. replaced pressure and return hydraulic lines on engine. replaced case drain line on engine iaw amm 29-11-51. accomplished system a hydraulic flush iaw motor control module 29-93-01. hydraulics system serviced. accomplished an engine run iaw amm 71-00-00. left eak check and operation check ok on the ground.

ship 5638 - air turn back - on climb, flight crew experienced right engine vibrations, decision made to return to sea. mtc found meta left in the tailpipe. corrective action : remove and replace #2 engine per amds work cards. ops and leak check okay.

fuel leak from nr 1 engine, fuel dripping from fan cowl on arrival. aircraft grounded. alternate de-activation procedures used per mpm chapter 5 table 3 item 9. found fuel present on-line coming from out of fuel pump, line wet under clamp, cleaned area, idle ran engine. no leaks observed. ran engine above 80 % n1, found fuel leaking from fuel out tube at the fuel oil heat exchanger for intergrated drive generator. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine fuel line from fuel out tube at the fuel oil heat exchanger and intergrated drive generator oil cooler iaw amm 73-11-06-400-801-f00, step 3f. ground ran engine above 80 % n1 again no leaks noted. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : none part name : line part condition : leaking

fuel leak checklist illumnated followed standard operation procedure, diverted, confered with inbd flight crew. fuel flow on right engine 1800 lbs per hour higher than left engine before shutdown. right engine exhaust gas temperature 40 degrees higher than left engine. right engine shutdown in-flight wind milled for 30 min before landing positive oil pressure 17 pounds per square inch - 21 pounds per square inch while engine was in windmill condition. noted. visually inspected p4.95 plumbing. no discrepancies noted. verified no additional ( applicable ) maintenance messages. add emp : 10 4300 interigated cmcf last leg report found maintenance message 73-08102. fim task 73-28-00-810-821-n00 partially accomplished. accomplished visual inspection of p2t2 sensor. no discrepancies unable to leak check p2t2 or p4.95 plumbing due

divert inflight shutdown declared emergency, suspect fuel leak nr 1 engine. comply wqrh. shutdown nr 1 engine, windmil left for approximately 30 min. right & right high pressure turbine active clearance control valve per amm.

air turn back, inflight shutdown right engine surge followed by fire indication passing 14k. ran qrh, discharged 2 fire bottles into right engine. fire extinguished after 3 minutes. exhaust gas temperature reached 1100 exhaust gas temperature. engine replaced.

on descent into kcvg, lt engine stuck at idle and would not accelerate as commanded. emergency declared. in accordance with engine failure checklist, complied with in-flight shutdown with a restart. engine restarted normally, but still at idle. approach and landing into destination airport kcvg without incident. aircraft was grounded for unscheduled maintenance. inspection of lt engine mec revealed broken vsv cable bellcrank. removed and replaced vsv feedback bellcrank, cables and var stator actuator. operational engine runs satisfactory. leak check satisfactory. no further defects noted. aircraft released to service. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : cable part condition : deteriorated

aircraft was grounded : at approximately 10,000 feet engine 2 overheat light illuminated. engine 1 fire light and engine 1 overheat does not test. returned to field. * supplemental report : replaced chafed harness mw0325 ( aala202106189013 ) pe right amm 26-11-02 and amm 26-10-01. replaced engine and auxiliary power unit fire and overheat detection control module ( aala202106219002 ) per amm 26-10-01.

captain called on satcom to report compressor stall on right engine. engine pulled back to idle to keep electric on-line but was not shutdown. emergency delcared, ac diverted to snn, landed overweight. the aircraft was grounded. replaced the nr 2 engine iaw mm 71-00-02, wc sec12 iaw 71-95-18. engine ran iaw 71-94-08. all engine parameters were normal. air & electrical were normal. no eicas messages noted.

fuel imbalance, followed by verified fuel leak nr 1 engine. performed unexpected fuel config, unwanted fuel transfer check, examine & cleaned jet pump nozzles ( no debris noted ), operation check both auto shut-off valves, performed tank compensator test, and performed engine idle leak check iaw amm and fim.

( toga engaged ). maintenance accomplished test 8 acceleration check iaw amm 71-00-00-700-824. acceleration within limits.

system a hydraulic quantity indication. emergency was declared, and landed without further incident. system a engine driven pump illuminated for duration of flight, greater than 5 minutes. the aircraft was grounded. replaced left engine hydraulic pump iaw amm 29-11-11. replaced all pressure, return, engine and emdp filter case. replaced emdp per amm 29-11-21. replaced pressure and return hydraulic lines on engine. replaced case drain line on engine iaw amm 29-11-51. accomplished system a hydraulic flush per motor control module 29-93-01. hydraulics system serviced. accomplished engine run iaw amm 71-00-00. leak check and operations checked ok on the ground.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports 15 min after takeoff passing fl200 right engine overheat light illuminated. reduced engine to idle, light extinguished. emergency declared, returned to dfw. maintenance troubleshot iaw fim 26-10-00-810-811 and found leak on hpt cooling duct. removed and replaced duct iaw em 72-54-11-300, leak check good. performed high powe right engine run for 10 min, no overheat indications. ok for service.

aircraft was grounded : left engine n1 indication did not reach planned setting of 95.3 % for takeoff. disconnected autothrottle while accelerating down the runway. pushed left throttle full forward and achieved approximately 91.2 % n1. aircraft was accelerating normally and takeoff was continued. all other indications on both engines appeared to be normal. left engine n1 indications appeared to correct itself shortly after takeoff and autothrottle were placed on. replaced left engine n1 speed sensor and accomplished a satisfactory ope rational check per amm 77-11-01.

after engine start, the left engine exhaust gas temperature continued to rise to 810 degrees, then engine flamed out. n1, n2, & n3 decreased to 0. fuel lever was placed to cutoff, ground crew advised flames coming from exhaust and went out by itself. found a bad bvcu, right & right bvcu iaw amm 75-32-01. also suspect ffg, removed and replaced the nr 1 ffg iaw amm 73-21-01, leak checked good. performed tests 1, 3, 2, 9, 10, 11, & 13 iaw mm 71-00-00, all checked good. performed borescope inspection on the nr 2 engine iaw fim 71-05-00-815-823-r00, hot section ( hpt, ipt, low pressure turbine and combustion chamber ) iaw amm 72-00-00. no damage found. nature of condition : engine flame out, warning indication, flame fire precautionary procedure : return to block part name : control unit part condition : faulted

during taxi out, a passing aircraft reported a fire in the right engine. no fire indications in the cockpit. the crew pulled the nr 2 engine fire handle, but did not activate the fire extinguishers. returned to gate without further inci dent. the aircraft was grounded. maintenance reinstated the nr 2 engine fire handle iaw amm 26-21-00, & accomplished a nr 2 engine fire detection system ops test iaw amm 26-11-00, & fire bottle inspection iaw amm 26-20-00. replaced the nr 2 engine.

in descent as the plane was leveling off at fl 340 and throttles coming up, right engine stayed at 40 % and began to stal left ( mild chugging ) froom right engine. right & right hydro mechanical unit per amm.

no.4 engine right thrust reverser forward web angle for plastic rub strip upper corner cracked.

on descent into destination station kcvg, lt engine stuck at idle and would not accelerate as commanded. emergency declared. in accordance with engine failure checklist, complied with in-flight shutdown with a restart. engine restarted normally, but still at idle. approach and landing into destination airport kcvg without incident. aircraft was grounded for unscheduled maintenance. inspection of lt engine mec revealed broken vsv cable bellcrank. removed and replaced vsv feedback bellcrank, cables and var stator actuator. operational engine runs satisfactory. leak check satisfactory. no further defects noted. aircraft released to service. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : bellcrank part condition : broken

passing through 15000 feet we received reverse video low engine oil quantity at 4 quarts. we ran qrh and returned to pdx. oil quantity increased to 6 quarts on descent and approach. it then dropped to 3 quarts on final approach. oil temperature en tire time never got above approximately 125deg center we did not shut the engine down. grounded - yes. air turn back. diversion time 14 minutes - removed and replaced #1 engine. aircraft released from etops restriction.
on aircraft inbound, found left engine fuel valve message appeared on engine shutdown. light and message cleared. ops normal. found no faults. placed fuel ignition control relay on order with mcc.

after takeoff passing 1000 ', 5 in succession loud bangs with heavy shutters. engine indications appeared normal and the re was no yaw associated with the bang shuttering. during nr 2 engine inlet and exhaust inspection found left hand fan stator aft inner segment panel at 11 : 00 position blew off and departed aircraft, left thrust reverser half damaged as well. thrust reverser damage is a gouge on interior wall about 9 : 00 position. gouge is approximately 6 " longitude by 5 " wide and into the honeycomb structure. pictures of damage attached. reverser right & right on separate write-up. wri 78-300645. checked environmental control unit 2a and environmental control unit 2b, no current faults and no faults stored in fault review. installed missing nr 2 fan stator inner aft liner segment

on climb out at approximately flight level 190, the crew heard a boom and smelled a strong smoke odor. at the same time, the airplane yawed and shuttered. the right engine had high exhaust gas temperature ( 1100 deg ) and n2 indication ( 113.1 ). the right engine was shutdown and the crew declared an emergency. the airplane was removed from service ( grounded ) and metal particles were found in the tail pipe. the right engine was replaced. the cause of the engine failure is unknown.

lost oil in both engines. an emergency was declared and aircraft landed without incident. on lift off left engine oil went to reverse and showed 3 quantitys, leveled at 10,000 ft. qrh has unsatisfactory remain level in hopes quantity would increase. quantities never got above 7 on left or 8 on right, opted to return to sea since oil pressure and temperatures were norm al. had an overweight landing at 164,000. performed oil service on #1 and #2 engines, opened cowls and performed run on both engines, no leaks noted. ( per operations manual loss of indication is a phenomenom called gulping oil, oil can dec rease as much as 11 quarts oil. indication was 9 and 10 on gauge at sea. aircraft is ok for service.

at rotation nr 2 engine fuel filter bypass illuminated. stayed on for about 15 minutes. aircraft grounded. on arrival, the nr 2 engine fuel bypass light not illuminated. removed and replaced the filter, no contamination noted on filter and leak checked good iaw amm 73-11-02-000-801. performed electronic engine controllers built in test equipment check and found fuel filter signal disagree and electronic engine controllers test passed iaw amm 73-21-00. removed and replaced the nr 2 engine fuel differential pressure switch iaw amm 73-34-01. operation check good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : pressure switch part condition : failed

due to recent report of 7 quarts oil add to the nr 2 engine while the aircraft is in storage. it is suspected that the engine indicating e may be over serviced due to a leaking anti-leak valve and lube unit scavenge ability. grounded - yes. removed and replaced oil anti-leak valve ref amm 79-21-09 on nr 2 engine. leak check good.

found section of bracket on thrust reverser side broken. bracket holds stand off for pre-cooler duct. removed and replaced the nr 2 engine, inbd thrust reverser half iaw specific 73-7830-9-0014. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : none part name : bracket part condition : broken

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports climbing thru 8-9000ft large bang left engine with aircraft shaking, indications indicated engine shutting down. check list followed to shutdown engine. fa reports large bang with electric power left side going off. emergency was declared. maintenance accomplished a borescope inspection, found damage to the 7th stage high pressure compressor. an engine change has been declared. supplemental information : maintenance removed and replaced engine iaw job card 71-94-01. ( closed )

after takeoff, right engine temperature reached 888 and indicator was red. emergency declared. right & right the nr 2 engine iaw amm 71-00-02. nature of condition : over temperature, warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : engine part condition : overtemp

nr 1 engine fire loop test failed for loop a. fault light and nr 1 engine fire light would not illuminate during test. during troubleshooting found a broken wire off terminal lug at m1760. replaced the terminal lug iaw swpm. left engine fire det system now ops normal. iaw amm 26-11-00-410-801. nature of condition : no test precautionary procedure : none part name : wire part condition : broken

during start of the nr 2 engine, had no light off or fuel flow. aborted start and followed qrc and qrh procedures. aircraft grounded. accomplished electronic engine controllers built in test equipment, observed fault message 73-31522, attempted to start the nr 2 engine observed both engine valve and spar valve lights transition and extinguish. no fuel flow observed. removed and replaced nr 2engine hydro mechanical unit. no leaks noted, no faults, operation check good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : hydro mechanical unit part condition : failed

aircraft was grounded : left engine hydraulic pump low pressure light illuminated, flight declared emergency and landed without further incident. replaced left engine driven pump with serviceable unit iaw amm 29-11-11-400-801-001, operation check good.

noticed excessive fuel burn on three consecutive waypoints, shortly thereafter recieved a level 2 fuel qty used check, possible fuel leak. ran qrh prcedure and the nr 2 tank or engine isolated as source of leak. further troubleshooting determined it was the nr 2 engine. shutdown the nr 2 engine iaw qrh. visually inspected the fuel line & found the elbow cracked. the elbow was removed and replaced iaw amm 28-21-01-4. tested ok, aircraft ok for service.

aircraft 7109 flight 9953 nrt msp is diverting to anc due to lt engine oil qty is dropping. this a position ferry from heavy check. flight crew only on-board. no emergency declared. sending sea to investigate. corrective action : removed aft center body & center vent tube to inspect for coking. no new leaks found. found #1 engine starter coated with fresh oil. remove and replace ' d #1 engine starter per b777 amm 80-11. high power leak check performed per b777 amm 71-00h01. no leaks noted.

left engine fuel filter eicas message came on during climb. eicas message came on and off several times and remained on th roughout. most off the flight. lt engine vibrated and vibration increased during descent complied with non-normal and no rmal checklists declared an emergency and returned to can. filter element checked normal, no contamination. installed the new fuel filter element. wiring check no abnormal found. replaced fuel filter differential pressure switch. performed left engine high power run, all parameters normal.

after takeoff, received simu tian ous lt engine overheat and engine fire, both on eicas with master warning and aural warning. performed inspection of the nr 1 engine iaw mm 72-00-00. found plug on tcc valve loose and leaking out onto fire loop. secured the leak and checked tcc valve, no leaks noted iaw amm 71-00-00. replaced the lt overheat detection wires iaw wd 26-11-12, & swpm 20-10-11. performed lt engine fire detection overheat system test, tested ok iaw amm 26-11-00. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : valve part condition : unsecure

while accompishing tc 78472022 ( sdi borescope engine hpt blade ) found 1 low pressure turbine nozzle with 1 full crack, 1 radial crack th at intersects with the f00000nopartull crack, a hole in hte low pressure turbine nozzle where the cracks intersect, and airfoil material lifting off forward of the hole. on the #1 engine. esn 894851. grounded - yes. removed and replaced #1 engine. defect transferred to shop wo 1165100.

aircraft was not grounded. during climb at high thrust setting, fuel flow 77,000 lbs, the left engine fuel filter bypass light illuminated. light went out with fuel flow less than 5000 lbs. removed and replaced left engine fuel filter iaw sic 4907. leak and operational check good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : none part name : filter part condition : unserviceable

aircraft in base visit : maintenance reports nr 2 engine runs after fuel control. switch off for 30 sec. maintenance removed and replaced #2 engine fuel flow governor iaw card 19l40073001, ops and leak check good. right enging shutdown on command.

auxiliary power unit autoshutdown event on gate with flame out exhaust pipe during event. mechanical failure of turbine, nature of condition : flame fire, engine stoppage precautionary procedure : other part name : engine part condition : failed

repeat borescope inspection on #1 engine with one low pressure turbine stage 1 nozzle vane with full crack and missing material less than. burned material has progress from. grounded - yes. removed and replaced #1 engine ref wo 1042103.

inflight shutdown declared emergency, fuel leak nr 1 engine verified by qrh procedure 500lb imbalance in 24 minutes. performed nr 1 engine shutdown. declared emergency landing normal. right & right e1 high turbine pressure active clearance control per amm.

at top of climb left engine stuck in climb setting no throttle response be it full or idle. completed qrh idle 12.2.5 and 12.2.10 engine. normal shutdown. landing weight 122.2. during ts discovered left throttle push pull cable rod had come lo ose from fcu. power lever crank. secured throttle push pull to fuel control unit power lever crank iaw m80 76-11-00. functional check normal.

on arrival, com left and com right both had a intermittant sound in headsets. speakers were on, turned off, no change. tried left & right indepedant ly - no-com. swithced to center to regain air traffic control flight coms. right com worked after landing. ts found left very high frequency thrust reverser inop and not testing. removed and replaced left thrust reverser per amm 23-12-01-4 ops checks normal ok for service. left thrust reverser mfg pn 822-1287-101 sn off 770xb and on 2rfdr.

nr 2 engine would not develop climb thrust out of 10,000 feet, returned to departure. right & right the nr 2 engine hydro mechanical unit iaw mt. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : hydro mechanical unit part condition : faulty

aircraft was grounded : left engine oil qty indication low with oil pressure fluctuating in precautionary amber zone, flight declared emergency and diverted to rdu. * supplemental report : replaced sealol seal ( aala202111110783 ) with new at n2 drive pad on left engine iaw amm 72-60-00 and replaced left engine with serviceable unit iaw workcard 08l40072003, leak and operation check good. will be submitted.

nr 2 engine right thrust reverser forward frame lower ballscrew actuator housing support bracket is cracked. fabricated and installed repair do ubler on nr 2 right thrust reverser forward lower frame housing per cmm 78-32-02 repair 16.

nr 1 engine outboard thrust reverser hold open rod requires replacement. replaced iaw amm 20-11-00. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : other part name : rod part condition : not reported

ship 697 - ( air turn back inflight shutdown ) on departure from atl crew performed air turn back due to left engine compressor stall and roll ba ck. corrective action : mtc found permanent magnet alternator rotor failure. windmill and borescope inspections performed. foqa data reviewed. mt center replaced permanent magnet alternator seal rotor and stator. shop performed gearbox inspections and concentricity and run out checks complied with. idle and high power engine runs good. aircraft returned to service.

aircraft was grounded. emergency declared. fll dfw flight. on taxi, the left engine was leaking fuel. shutdown engine and shut-off boost pumps. aircraft towed to gate. removed and replaced nr 1 high pressure turbine active clearance control valve iaw amm 75-21-00. leak and operational check good. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : engine shutdown part name : control valve part condition : faulty

aircraft not grounded : while on taxi. flight crew from a following aircraft reported fire emanating from no. 2 engine breather tube. maintenance inspected #2 engine iaw amm 71-00-00-800-803 f00 and found okay for service.

aircraft was grounded : flight diverted to stl on account of low oil quantity in the number two engine. emergency declared. maintenance removed and replaced right engine oil qty transmitter iaw amm 79-31-01. leak check & ops checks good.

replacement of coroded #2 engine mount fitting. to replace corroded aft engine mount fitting and tee chords at #2 engine indicating e position. remove and replace #2 engine support fitting pn 65-18670-1, chords pn 65-31281-3, 65-31281-4, 65-22913-5, 65-22913-6, and web of #2 engine mount support structure.

at top of cruise got a left engine fuel filter eicas. emergency declared. ts per fim 73-34 fault tree 803. changed nr 1 engine fuel filter ref amm 73-11-02. leak check good. message did not return on idle run. right & right nr 1 engine fuel pump differential pressure switch per amm 73-34-01. leak and operation check normal. no message. showing at this time. nature of condition : false warning precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : pressure switch part condition : faulty

during takeoff, the nr 1 engine engine pressure ratio gauges match up, but n1, exhaust gas temperature, n2, n3, ff were 30 % less. the aircraft climbed out and continued to have assembly metric thrust and passed 10k ft altitude engines continued to run about 30 percent apart with not much thrust to climb. at that point, decided to return to base. inspected the nr 1 engine p1 probe, and found debris clogging the probe inlet. removed all debris and inspected p1 probe mm 73-21-04-6. nature of condition : false warning precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : probe part condition : obstructed

aircraft was grounded : right engine anti ice light illuminated after takeoff, flight declared emergency and returned to field. replaced engine anti ice valve with serviceable unit iaw amm 30-21-11, operation check good.

aircraft was grounded : aircraft taxing behind unsatisfactory reported flames coming from tail pipe on no.2 engine, no indication in-flight deck. inspected #2 engine inlet and exhaust iaw fim 71-05-00 no damage noted. flight crew ran engine at idle all checks normal ; ok for service iaw fim 71-05-00.

rejected takeoff at approximately 70 knots, the right engine compressor stall. fire crews confirmed no fire. taxi back to gate was uneventful. found metal in the tail pipe and the fan seized. removed and replaced the nr 2 engine. ops and leak checked good. nature of condition : partial rpm power loss, warning indication precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : engine part condition : failed

returned to departure due to the left engine oil quantity was decreasing. replaced the engine. nature of condition : warning indication, fluid loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : oil system part condition : leaking

overtemp on #1 during relight, shutdown at fl 400. relight at fl 310. via qrh " in-flight ". ref item #1 : crew reported th at aircraft was approaching fuel imbalance. crew shut-off left fuel pumps, forgot to select crossfeed. as they were going to select crossfeed, left engine flamed out. on first engine restart, exhaust gas temperature exceeded limits. 788 exhaust gas temperature for 13 seconds total. crew shutdown engine, exhaust gas temperature was at 30 degrees center at second engine restart, attempt successful. removed and replaced #1 and #2 igniter plugs iaw amm 74-21-02. cw fim 71-10 ft 810, all checks good.

after takeoff right engine vibration was felt throughout the airplane with n1 up to 5.1 and oil pressure fluctuation between 70-135 pounds per square inch. during decent vibration indication lowered to 4.1 and back-up to 5.1. accomplished lp fan blade re sort per engineering. accomplished motor control module 71-94-10, all parameters within amm limits. the aircraft was grounded. nature of condition : vibration buffet precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : blade part condition : out of position

after start left bleed off eicas message was displayed bleed switch light also illuminated. aircraft back to block and grounded by maintenance. removed & replaced #1 engine pressure shutoff valve iaw b767 amm 36-11-09. ops & leak check good ; performed left engine run iaw amm 71-00-00 ; operation check normal. aircraft returned to service

at cruise altitude left fuel gauge indicated 400 lbs less than right fuel gauge. fuel used on left engine indicated 3.85 & right engine indicated 3.90. all other indications appear normal. flight level 310,. ff left 2.93, ff right 2.94, vibration left 0.5 vibration right 0.4, sat - 49 ' center. 400 lbs imbalance occurred 30 mins at cruise altitude. grounded - yes. performed fqis procedure test. current status - no present faults. in-flight fault fault history - no faults. ground test - passed per fim 28-41 task 801. per tech services performed engine fuel feed pumps functional test. check ok per amm 28-22-00.

advancing thrust for takeoff, a report was received from another aircraft that flames were observed from tailpipe and side of engine. engine indications were normal. after exiting runway and securing the engine, fire chief reported no indication of fire or smoke. accomplished fim 71-05-00-810-811-f00. found the engine to be acceptable for continued ser vice. the aircraft was grounded.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports two compressor stalls below 500 while on approach to mia. the first one felt like the left engine the second one sounded like the right engine. maintenance troubleshot and accomplished fim task 71-05-00. removed and replaced the left engine & right cit sensor iaw amm 73-21-02. accomplished high power assurance run at all power setting iaw 71-00-00, all parmeters were normal, no eicas messages noted. ( see sdr # aala201906089002 )

#1 engine selected engine anti ice on - however yellow tai illuminated next to #1 engine n1 gauge and blue cowl valve open light stayed on bright. landing wt 150,100 lbs rate of decent less than 200 ' feet per minute. grounded - yes. removed and replaced #1 engine col tai valve, leak and operation check good. ref b737-900 amm 30-21-11. opened, collard, re-set 2 circuit-breaker ' s p18-3 row a col 6,7. bonding check good. performed overweight landing inspection. ref amm 05-51-35. max landing weight within limits. no defects noted.

white smoke reported by tower. engine indications normal, except nr 1 engine fuel flow a bit higher and fuel consumption 50 lbs per minute higher than left. diverted. the aircraft was grounded. maintenance removed and replaced the nr 1 engine hpt acc iaw amm 75-21-01.

cruise fl370 scanning over-head prior to descent. observed right electronic engine controllers alteration in mode switch. no accompany eicas. referenced qrh, decided to put both electronic engine controllers in same mode " alteration ". accomplished qrh. upon pushing throttles up n1 and exhaust gas temperature began fluxing. ff at idle would not go below 4.0 and as we descended it would climb. at 13,000 ft ff was approximately 11.2 and we could not descend. fuel was at approximately 10.5. looked for other relief in qrh could not find any. at this point engine was not contr ollable. followed qrh in shutting down right engine. declared emergency prior to shutting engine down. windmilled for 10-15 min. right & right engine environmental control unit as per mm 73-21-15-4, all test pass also right & right control alternator as per mm 73-21-08-4-3 all test pa
during start left engine spar valve light did not illuminate. engine stabilized and shutdown by itself. removed and replaced left spar valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. operation check good.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports left throttle very stiff binding with screeching noise when autothrottle on. main tenance reports number 1 throttle control lever failed force check. removed and replaced engine thrust module iaw amm 76 - 11-01. test and operation check accomplished all satisfactory. ok for service.

aircraft was grounded. aircraft diverted to cle account of number 1 engine shutdown ( failure ). oil pressure was 0 pounds per square inch oil qty was 17, we had n-1 and n-2 rotation performed emergency shutdown check list. accomplished electronic engine controllers nr 1 built in test equipment found severa left faults including fmv demand and position signals disagree, the vbv demand and position signals disagree, fuel flow was not detected, hptacc demand & position signals disagree. an emergency was declared and flight landed without incident. single engine time reported as 20 minutes. removed engine sn 874880 and installed esn 874831 at lt position on cle bow dated 10222018.

on t-off actuator informed unsatisfactory a piece of aluminum metal part was found on the runway. inspected and found nr 1 engine cna aft in ner skin missing. installed serviceable common nozzle assembly. engine closed and thrust reverser ops ck good. aircraft ok for service.

ref so 1010104 nr-00001, during re-inspect of #2 engine esn 896776 low pressure turbine nozzles found progression in cracks, 5 each ful left cracks radial cracks on 2 intersecting, crack on 3, and 1 airfoil with 2 holes. requires replacement of engine ref b73 7-800 amm 72-00-00-200-811-f00 fig 634 sheet 4. grounded - yes. removed and replaced #2 engine ref ebu shop wo 1038248

on climbout from kchs between 11000-12000 ft, right fire engine warning came on. disconnected autothrottle and reduced power to idle. all engine indications were normal at all times. warning went out during reduction in pwer. flight with right engine at id leading edge. found damaged to upper cowl and center upper anti ice duct, repaced nowe cowl anti ice duct pn 13277-503. leak cks good. cw gvi of engine and exterior components, oll ok. replaced upper cowl ref log 6860836. ran engine, all ok. aircraft ok for service. according to the mcc noto fication, an emergency was declared. ( lp6860834 )

aircraft was grounded : flight returned to ont on account of left engine oil bypass light illuminated. an emergency was declared. maintenance found coke carbon particles on the scavenge filter. removed and replaced left engine scavenge oil filter iaw amm 79-21-06, leak check good. removed and replaced left engine scavenge oil filter transmitter iaw amm 79-21-07, leak check good. accomplished mcd and scavenge screens inspection iaw amm 79-00-00, leak check good. all checks good.

fuel dripping from nr 2 engine. inspected nr 2 engine drains, found right vsv drain leaking, ran engine, fuel leak stopped. no evidence of leaking post run, aircraft ok for service. fuel leak must be addressed within 25 flight cycles iaw amm 71 - 71-00-200-801-500. grounded - yes. removed and replaced the right vsv actuator iaw amm 75-31-01 operation check good, no lea ks noted.

during climb at aprox fl200, a loud bang and a two second longitude shutter was felt throughout aircraft. climbed to fl300 iaw air traffic control, aprox 235 knots indicated air speed. airplane required two deg left aileron trim for wings level up to flaps 20 deg. at flaps 30 deg. on final, aileron trim 0 deg. fa reported a flash out of left engine immediately after shutter was felt. accomplish a nr1 engine run, power and acceleration, deceleration test. [ 1 ]. accomplished fim 71-05 fault 803. accomplished nr 1 engine borescope iaw amm 72-00-00-846-328 and no damage was noted. performed variable stator vane system check iaw amm 71-08-809. no discrepancies noted. performed engine test iaw amm 71-00-00201 and engine power and acceleration test, iaw amm nature of condition : vibration buffet precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : unknown part condition : unknown

at level off at fl350, cost index 5, as autothrottle pulled back to cruse mach we felt two quick thuds in succession. fa ' s called to report the same no unusual engines indications noted. jumpseating pilot thinks issue came from #1 side. suspected possible compressor stall. right & right #1 engine bleed air check valve per amm.
flight crew report fuel drip from nr 2 engine. grounded - yes. replaced nr 2 engine right vsv actuator per amm 75-31-01. leak and ops test good. plt cleared.

fire eicas status left engine. fire overheat detection card fault or failure, or aims loss of arinc 629429. removedand replaced lt engine fire detection card iaw amm 26-11-03. performed engine fire detection operational test iaw amm26-11-00. test passed. no further messages. nature of condition : false warning precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : circuit card part condition : failed

left engine valve did not illuminate when fuel control moved from cut off to run. found debris inside of the light, cl eaned and replaced the lamp, pressure to check ok, tested left fuel valve solenoid and light iaw amm 71-00-00, removed and right eplaced lt engine valve annunciator light iaw amm 33-16-02 and operation check ok iaw amm 71-00-00.

etops event slc jfk. performed a rejected takeoff at 100 knots due to left engine lack of acceleration. engine would no t go higher than 87 %. corrective action : maintenance replaced the fuel filter and installed hydro mechanical unit. system operation is normal.
left fuel flow indication inop. ( no calculated fuel on fms ). replaced w13 harness on nr 1 engine iaw amm 73-21-18. fuel flow check during engine runs iaw amm 71-00-00.

left engine oil quanitty began dropping shortly after cruise. loss increased in rate to approximately 1 quart per 30 minutes. at 4 quarts diverted. all other parameters within limits. arf reported something leaking after landing. engine. engine has been changed iaw card 71-94-01. aircraft was grounded.

fuel leak on right side after center pumps off more than 2000lb split in 20 mins. fuel imbalance reported lt main 13.7rt main 9.8 and config light on. stuck both tanks confirmed imbalance, performed test of the engine x-feed valves iaw amm 28-22-02-714-055 & amperage ; 28-22-02-790-801 & defueling valve leak test iaw amm 28-26-01-790-801. no faults noted. ref fim. 28-21-00-810-801 complied with test of shut-off valves, crossfeed valves, fuel fill and defuel valves, engine fuel feed and refuel manifold test all found no faults. performed engine runs on left and right engine no leaks noted ref amm 73-11-07-404-019. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : unknown part condition : malfunctioned

aborted takeoff below 80 knots due to the crew reporting that they lost the right bleed system. also reported that during engine start on both engines, the bleed lights flickered. during advancing the throttles, both bleed lights remained out and the bleeds stabilized. performed a pneumatic health check and found the high pressure shut off valve faulted. replaced the high pressure shut off valve and hi stage pilot as a precaution. performed a revers flow controller, isolation valve and operation check iaw amm.

nr 1 cowl valve open bright blue disagree light illuminated when engine anti ice positioned on. thrust was at idle. aircraft grounded. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine cowl tai valve iaw amm 30-21-11. ops and leak checked good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : other part name : valve part condition : failed

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports on descent left engine went to 2.0 to 2.3, at flight idle then began to fluctuate. maintenance reports vibration within limits iaw amm 71-00-00. * supplemental information : maintenance accomplished #1 engine fan balance iaw card 77-95-12.

during start of the nr 2 engine. fuel found leaking. ground crew reported fuel leak during and after start. aircraft grounded. performed engine vents and drain inspection on the nr 2 engine. ran the nr 2 engine two times at idle power. fuel leaking during start and stopped 2 minutes into the run from fuel pump drain line valve body. removed fuel pump iaw amm73-11-01-000-801. with fuel pump on bench, split fuel pump from hydro mechanical unit iaw tc n8473000, installed a serviceable fuel pump to hydro mechanical unit iaw tc n8473001. installed fuel pump to gearbox iaw amm 73-11-01-400-801 f00. accomplished an idle leak check test 3a, actuators test nr 12 and electronic engine controllers built in test equipment test nr 13, all tests passed iaw tc n8473001. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : return to block part name : pump part condition : leaking
discrepancy - left engine bleed surges on descent corrective action - removed and replaced left engine hs pilot iaw amm 36-11-08. leak check and operation check ok.

aircraft had a loud bang and moved to the left. passengers heard and felt the noise. after 10 minutes all left engine parameters surged back and forth. iaw amm 79-21-05, lt engine oil system magnetic chip detector check and service. accomplished vsv actuation hardware for damage and examined the vbv actuation hardware for damage iaw 75-31-03-216-002-h00 and 75-32-01-206-005-h00. accomplished power assurance run and verify left engine paramerters are normal. the aircraft was grounded.

while taxiing out for takeoff, several other pilots following our aircraft, reported seeing a 3 to 4 foot orange flame extending aft out of the exhaust area of the nr 1 engine when engine power was pushed up beyond idle. flight deck engine instruments were normal. aircraft grounded. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine lube unit iaw amm 79-21-01-000-801-f00, and 79-21-01-400-801-f00. leak and ops tested good. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : other part name : lubrication unit part condition : leaking

flight 101 en route lhr - jfk. aircraft was grounded. lt engine fire indication at cruise. shutdown the lt engine, declared an emergency, and diverted to dub. fire handle was pulled, fire extinguisher was not discharged. landed without further incident. single engine time was 28 minutes. fire ovht detector right core shorted, replaced right core fire detector assembly iaw amm 26-11-01-000-812-003 & carried out iaw amm 26-11-00-710-801, message clrd and a positive fixed, ok for service. ref lp 12160592 - #2 engine fire warning light does not test. grounded - yes. ref tsr 703262 for troubleshooting cw built in test equipment t estimate ref fim 26-10 task 801. no faults found. reracked m279 module in e&e bay, ref amm 26-10-00 no help. while checking center kpt fire panel fasteners system suddenly tested ok. removed panel cycled #2 fire handle and cleaned and reinstalled panel. cw engine fire loop resistance test ref amm 26-11-00 all resistances checked good. cw detailed visual inspection of harness and detectors, no defects noted. complied with gvi on #2 engine fan and core fire detectors and harness terminal connections. no defects noted. at this time #2 engine fire warning good. due to history replaced m279, engine and auxiliary power unit

engine fuel indication fuel used indication not normal, fuel flow normal engine 1 at top of climb fuel qty 7.9 left and 8. all 6 pumps on w center thrust reverser tank fuel. per crew. fuel on dest. decreased en route. getting worse with performed fqis built in test equipment procedure per fim 28-41 task 801. built in test equipment found maintenance message 28-41108 hitting on legs 1-13 and time. fuel flow normal on both engines. showed tank #1 degraded with maintenance message 28-41108 compensator data 14-25. no water contamination in fuel tank and no microbial bad. also, stick readings are out of tolerence with flight deck growth present. ref fim ta ck 28-41 task 807. fuel qty indicators on both left and right tanks. replaced #1 tank compensator ref amm 28-41-21. fqis

aircraft not grounded : pilot reports left engine slow to shutdown, when fuel control switch moved to cutoff, approx.15 seconds. recycled switch once. maintenance removed and cleaned connector on mec. reinstalled connector and operated engine indicating e. engine shuts down normally.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports right engine very slow to spool up on takeoff. also, at idle at altitude on descent leading edge aving fl 240, right fuel flow was 0.6 left was 1.1. took one and a half knobs on throttles to match ff n1 44.134.7. maintenance accomplished right engine vsv feedback cable adjustment test iaw job card 4455. found normal no adjustments needed. accomplished engine run iaw amm 71-00-00. found all parameters normal.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports two compressor stalls below 500 while on approach to mia. the first one felt like the left engine, the second one sounded like the right engine. maintenance troubleshot and accomplished fim task 71-05-0 0. removed and replaced the left & right engine cit sensor iaw amm 73-21-02. accomplished high power assurance run at all power setting iaw 71-00-00, all parmeters were normal. no eicas messages noted. ( see sdr # aala201906119014 )

during descent, approach and after engine shutdown, the left cowl valve open light flashed on and off intermittently. tai did not display with blue call light. aircraft grounded. performed fim 30-21 806 initial evaluation. operation check good. due to history, removed and replaced the nr 1 engine cowl tai valve iaw amm 30-21-11.

landed with fuel imbalance. performed fuel imbalance checklist in-flight fuel flow on no 1 engine was 500lb per hour higher. actual shutdown fuel was 300 lbs above flight plan for 2 hour flight. grounded - yes. accomplished fqis built in test equipment reference fim 28-41 task 801. no current status faults. interrogated inflight faults and fault history. no faults logged. performed crossfeed valve operational test reference amm 28-22-21. test normal. no imbalance message noted on cds. started both engine ' s ref amm 71-00-00 at idle nr 1 ff was ". fuel imbalance message did not show on cds. could not duplicate. no other defects noted.

right engine bleed off light on with also the right pack off light on during taxi. aircraft lined up for takeoff and right engine. bleed light did not extinguish during engine acceleration. aircraft aborted takeoff and returned to gate. maintenance groun dead ended aircraft. removed and replaced right pressure shutoff valve iaw amm 36-11-09. aircraft released for flight.

inspection type : na air turn back - aircraft taken oos. on up wind at 1509 msl level 2 hydraulic 3 fail emergency declared air turn back to secondary flight display center omplied with qrh procedures stowed both alt gear external handles 32-32-00. remove and replace crcked #3 engine left engine driven pump amm 29-11-20-400. remove and replace #3 engine left & right engine driven pump oil seal assembly amm 72-65-06-1401 ( rear ) & 72-65-07-1401 ( front ). remove and replace right side aft pump amm 29-11-20-401-2. right right filters at engine #3 hydraulic system manfld amm 29-12-41-201. perf. #3 engine hydraulic system manfld fltr lk ck & reinstall. cover amm 29-12 - 41. no lks noted

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports left engine would not shutdown with fuel control fire handle pulled. maintenance removed and replaced # 1 engine. fuel flow governor iaw job card 73-94-01. operation check normal.

diversion, leveling at fl 340 we felt a shudder and two pops. the nr 2 engine n1 rolled back to 53 % and the exhaust gas temperature, fuel flow & n2 decreased. found compressor blades torn. right & right nr 2 engine per mt. nature of condition : partial rpm power loss, warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : compressor blade part condition : torn

at fl390, the right engine overheat eicas indicator illuminated. emergency declared. found the nr 2 engine upper fire combustion & turbine case sensor mid clamp loose iaw fim task 26-11-00-815-803. secured the clamp iaw eipc 26-11-01 item 430. wrench checked all pressure shutoff valve & hs valve pneumatic duct clamps. accomplished duct leak check with foil, ran the nr 2 engine at high power several times with no overheat light displayed and no leaks noted. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : clamp part condition : loose
nr 2 engine right thrust reverser stiffener, forward of the cascade vane at 2 : 30 position was cracked. removed and replaced the stiffener iaw srm 54-01-42. minor.

during walk-around found nr 1 engine fuel leak. found fuel oil cooler line broken. right & right line, iaw amm 24-11-10. leak check pending. performed engine wet motor and engine run up, no leaks noted. operations check normal, iaw 71-00-00 ref leak check only. pn off : 1326m91g01, national stock number. found fuel leak from main pump strainer cover. removed and replaced pack ing, engine wet motor and run up operations check good. no leaks noted, iaw amm 73-11-01 and 71-00-00.

nr 2 engine spar valve light failed to illuminate when fuel control was selected to run. removed and replaced right engine fue left shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. performed operation check iaw amm 28-22-11. good, no faults at this time.
air turn back, pilot reported duct pressure gauge had a 20 % split with #2 indicating lower pressure. right & right #2 engine high stage valve per amm.

left engine, high exhaust gas temperature and fuel flow at 10,000 ft when changing power from climb 2 to normal climb. ran the qrh, continued to operate engine ( left ) at lower power and returned to airport. inspected nr 1 engine inlet and exhaust with no defects noted iaw mm 72-00-00-6, inspected the nr 1 engine master chip detector iaw mm 79-21-03-04, no defects noted. aircraft ok for continued service. nature of condition : false warning precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : warning message part condition : false activation

during cruise, about 1 : 40 hours into flight, red fire warning indication in both the right fuel control switch and right engine fire switch flickered on and off twice. no eicas messages and all engine indications were normal. the aircraft was grounded. accomplished fault isolation iaw fim 26-11-00 and present leg fault indicates failure of p84 a10 card failed. replaced a10 card in p84 iaw mm 26-10-00, and 26-11-00, and ea 283108a, ran right engine. operation check normal.

during taxi to the runway, passengers on-board a near by aircraft and air traffic control tower reported flames coming from left engine. engine was shutdown. the nr 1 engine has been replaced iaw motor control module 71-94-01. aircraft was grounded.

left engine fuel filter eicas, emergency declared, air turn back iaw fim 73-11-00-815. right & right the lt engine fuel filter & differential pressure switch iaw amm 73-34-01-024, & 73-11-02-004. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : pressure switch part condition : failed

inflight shutdown & air turn back, during climb to fl250 the left engine rolled back. crew followed qrh procedure for engine shutdown and returned to departure. mtc found permanent magnet alternator stator housing bolts loose and rotor and connectors damaged. carbon seal, rotor and stator replaced and gearbox run out checks performed. wire harness replacement in progress.

engine 2 flame out on decent. emergency declared. performed windmilling inspection. performed external inspection foll overwing exposure to fire extinguishing agent. did gvi of engine external components. did borescope inspection of combusti on chamber, hpt blades & vanes stages 1,2 and low pressure turbine stage blades. replaced fmv on #2 engine. leak and operation check satisfactory.

the aircraft was grounded. at fl250 on climbout, right engine exhaust gas temperature went into red zone with a high exhaust gas temperature. det fire engine right eicas message. right exhaust gas temperature indicated, then indicated a low exhaust gas temperature of 346 deg. the flight declared an emergency and returned to kmia without further incident. found blown borescope plug on right engine. replaced plug and replaced right engine lt reverser half iaw 78-94-10. also replaced many parts due to excessive heat. ok for service. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : plug part condition : blown

inspection type : na slight oily smell coming from the packs. more pronounced with the left pack on. at altitude oil pressure ure left engine 51, right engine 91.r+r left engine iaw tc #5001 ( rr ) ops and leak cked good. aircraft ok for service.

* emergency declared * right hydraulic system pressure and right hydraulic qty caution message on eicas. hydraulic qty. ref aipc clamp. installed filter module and components of the right engine driven pump 29-11-17-03 item 798 worn through at aft clamp and cracked. iaw amm 29-11-17. audio control panel ' d engine run and leak check, no leaks noted, removed filter module and components of the engine driven pump right side for aircraft returned to serviceable condition access of removal of pressure tube. installed new tube and aft add emp : 071184 correction, should read #2 engine pylon not #1.

fl350 mach. loud and heavy vibration. accomplished call out, visually inspected engine in and out and 2.9 bleed valves found no discrepencies iaw fim 71-05-00-810-819-n00. nature of condition : vibration buffet, warning indication, partial rpm power loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : engine part condition : surges

nr 1 engine failed to ignite during start. fuel flow was normal. aborted engine start iaw qrh. ignition switch was selected to right. aircraft grounded. removed and replaced the right ignition lead on the nr 1 engine iaw amm 74-21-01, and performed ignition system audible test iaw amm 74-00-00-750-801-f00. ops tested good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : lead part condition : failed

received a level 2 fuel qty used check caution, 1 hour into flight descending through fl340, on arrival. complied with qrh, declared emergency and landed. confirmed a fuel leak from the nr 1 engine. fuel shut off valve closed on the nr 3 engine afte right shutdown. right & right the pump to fuel control tube and gaskets iaw mm 73-12-01-4-1. leak checked good. ok for service.

on takeoff, after both engines were stabilized at 40 %, takeoff power applied and aircraft drifted to the right nearly off the runway. returned to the gate. accomplished #2 engine is slow to accelerate fault isolation per frmfim 73-05-00-810-814-f00. drained #2 engine ps3 line. found small quantity of water. replaced the nr 2 engine bleed air check valve per amm 36-11-02 which was found to be in serviceable condition. accomplished acceleration check test 8 per amm 71-00-00-700-824-f00. operational check good. aircraft was grounded. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : bleed valve part condition : failed

behind on fuel plan. wet motor engine ref 71-00-00-700-822-f00 ( leaking in-flight ). found right vsv drain leaking upon arrival at hanger, motor nr 2 engine and found fuel leaking from hptacc drain. right & right hptacc valve, ref amm 75-21-01. audio control panel nr 2 engine run and actuators test. all passed, no faults and leak check good.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports right throttle sticks at mid position. need to force it past mid position to set thrust. maintenance found right engine throttle control box has broken shield, blended edge of bracket, reinstalled rivets and verified throttle operation iaw ea 300983.
nr 1 engine throttle cracked at fastener mount hole for throttle knob. repaired handle iaw ea.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports throttle split on takeoff during climb split became 3 knobs, lt throttle almost at stop at 10,000ft throttles evened out, normal ops after that. maintenance reports #1 engine fuel pump replaced iaw amm 73 - 11-01 and job 73-94-12. ops and leak check ok.

lt engine bleed valve off light with associated left engine bleed and left pack off light. aircraft back to gate. aircraft grounded. verified pressure shutoff valve won ' t open, removed and replaced lt engine pressure shutoff valve. operations checked good, iaw b767 mm 36-11-1 8. remain etops 180.

aircraft was grounded : air interrupted back to hnl on account of engine bleed status message. flight was not overweight for landing and no emergency declared. left engine bleed off, started with status message left high pressure shut-off valve then engine indicating and crew alerting system left bleed off. replaced left hand high pressure fan air controller.

on short final, the left engine failed and appeared to be seized. ran engine fire severe damage check list & shut it down. continued single engine landing. emergency declared. landed safely on runway after with no further. incident. no emergency equipment was used. aircraft taken out of service. left engine replaced with iaw mfc 5001. system cks satisfactory.

nr 2 engine trend data shows a sudden increase in low pressure rotor vibration levels. data scatter indicates hardware inspection and fan relube required. - priority two - engine run required etops significant system. grounded - yes. found 5 each rubber stop elastomers on rear cone ring damaged. all 24 each shims missing about 90 % moly coating. found quantity of moly lube a bit heavy, dry & flakey. replaced 5 each rubber stop elastomers on rear cone spinner and removed and replaced all 24 shims on # 2 engine ref tc 78472002. accomplished fan blade lube on 32 engine iaw tc 78472002. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : other part name : spacer part condition : damaged

crew reported shortly after takeoff, the nr 1 engine oil qty dropped to zero with associated loss of oil pressure. inflight shutdown performed. emergency declared. found starter clamp broken. as a percaution, removed, replaced, and serviced the starter iaw amm 80-11-01. installed a new clamp. performed installation test iaw power plant test 71-00-00-800-811-f00.tested and leak checked good. nature of condition : warning indication, fluid loss precautionary procedure : unsched landing, engine shutdown part name : clamp part condition : broken

while taxiing, told that a flame was coming out of the nr 2 engine. declared an emergency and returned to the gate afte right securing the engine. maintenance visually examined the nr 2 engine exhaust area and found oil puddle and heavy soot insi de exhaust plug. iaw amm 71-00 this condition is described as a kind of candle fire phenomena. inspected flame arrestor with no trouble found, ran engine at idle for 20 with no flames noted.

left engine fire warning activated intermittently, eventually stopped before engine shutdown. emergency declared and flight landed without further incident. the aircraft was grounded. maintenance replaced hp2 and hp6 ducts iaw mm 36-11 - 01 and accomplished high power run iaw mm 71-00-00. no fire loop faults occured.

after passing 11,000 ft, received a level 3, nr 1 engine fire warning. followed qrh, and shutdown the nr 1 engine. un eventful landing. removed and replaced bracket and hp cooling recoup y duct iaw em 72-00-00, performed a high power run iaw jrh and leak checked normal. aircraft ok for service.

spar valve did not cycle during left engine start. replaced the lt engine fuel shut-off valve actuator iaw amm 28-22-11. operation check normal. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : return to block part name : actuator part condition : inoperative

the aircraft was grounded. diverted the flight due to a right engine aft sump chip detector indication. declared an emergency and landed without further incident. maintenance replaced the right engine lubrication unit. performed installation test, no leaks found iaw amm 79-21-01.

left engine fire warning activeated intermittently, eventually stopped before engine shutdown. emergency declared and landed without further incident. the aircraft was grounded. maintenance replaced hp2 and hp6 ducts iaw mm 36-11-01, and accomplished high power run iaw mm 71-00-00. no fire loop faults occured.

at 10,000, climbing in climb, power left engine fuel flow got high and exhaust gas temperature yellow. ran qrh and returned to airport. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine p1 probe iaw amm73-21-04-4, ops normal iaw 30-34-00-5. nature of condition : warning indication, over temperature precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : engine part condition : overtemp

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports that another aircraft reported left engine exhaust torching flames on taxi out. maintenance inspected engine #1 iaw amm 71-00-00. no defects noted. ok for service.

aircraft was grounded : pilot reports right engine rolled back to idle while slowing to. emergency declared. landed uneventfully. maintenance removed and replaced the engine fuel pump iaw amm 73-12-01. operation check good.

crew reported ? experienced several abnormal aircraft vibrations. discussed with crew. declared an emergency. landed at nearest suitable airport using normal procedures. usa jet maintenance was sent to kafw to troubleshoot problem. upon inspection of the #2 engine metal shavings were found in the inlet. the front accessory cover was removed, and it was found that the #1 bearing had failed. this was the cause of the vibration in-flight. the #2 engine is being replaced and the engine shop will seek to determine the cause of the #1 bearing failure. note : c1 fan disk was replaced at shop vis it which would have necessitated the inspection of the #1 bearing for serviceability. a supplemental report will be file

nr 1 engine smoking excessively at shutdown. fuel smell reported by ground crew and passengers. removed & replaced nr 1 engine fuel control per amm 7321. ran engine to power including accelerate checks. no smell or odors in cabin. engine checks no rmal per amm 71-00.

two foot flame reported out of the nr 1 engine nozzle on spool up at 40 %, went away at toga. tower reported flame, abort was accomplished at 40kts, the engine has been running for 5 or more minutes, no flight deck indications. aircraft grounded. accomplished fault isolation proceedures for accumulator in the center plug cavity iaw fim 71-05 task 811. no defects found with aft sump, flame arrestor inspected magnetic chip detector, showed no abnormal debris. accomplished electronic engine controllers built-in test equipment iaw fim 73-00 task 801. no faults found. ran aircraft engines to 80 pere cent for five minutes with maintenance visual on the nr 1 engine, no defects noted. visually inspected forward & aft nr 1 engine iaw fim 71-05 task 801. no defects noted. a nature of condition : flame fire precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : cover part condition : leaking

aircraft was grounded : pilot had to pull fire switch to shut engine down. after pulling fire handle engine. valve light sta yed on. maintenance removed and replaced fuel flow governor iaw job card 73-94-01. operation check good.

after takeoff, at aproximately 500 ft above ground level, experienced a loud bang from the left engine. the engine rolled back and exhaust gas temperature went to 659 and flashing. complied with qrh for compressor stall. landed with reduced thrust landing qrh checklist. an emergency was declared.

nr 2 engine inlet and fan blade detailed inspection. found both upper & lower attach brackets gouged from turn buckle on forward tube for tai valve. aircraft grounded. replaced tai duct on nr 2 engine and lower attachment and turn buckle iaw amm 30-21-11. leak check of nr 2 engine tai valve and duct good. nature of condition : other precautionary procedure : none part name : bracket part condition : gouged

( aircraft 7106, low pressure 1013189 ) on number 1 engine change found the thrust reverser cross tie assembly. bracket broken and stop s cracked. replaced cross tie brackets and stops on number 1 engine.

nr 1 engine rear flange assembly cracked at the intermediate bolt. aircraft grounded. removed and replaced the nr 1 engine rea right flange assembly iaw amm 72-56-00. secured.

during idle leak ck found fuel leaking from nr 1 engine servo fuel heater assembly. grounded - yes. removed and replaced the nr1 engine servo fuel heater per amm 73-11-07. fuel servo heater installation test passes, no leaks noted. nature of condition : fluid loss precautionary procedure : none part name : heater part condition : leaking

engine fuel feed system center-left ( right ) fuel pump eicas message shows and left ( right ) center pumps pressure light is on 02 right fuel center pump light came on wassoc eicas with 7.0 in center tank due to air return per crew debrief, both fuel pump off and right bleed off ( low pressure 4882556 ) happened exactly at the same time. ran right engine with aux pump as the fuel source and all ops ck ' d good, but was able to duplicate both discrepancies when n2 speed card circuit-breaker ' s were pulled. right & right engine n2 speed card m1092 per amm 73-21-54 and wdm 28-22-12, aux fuel pump cks good. ok to continue. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : unsched landing part name : circuit card part condition : unserviceable

aircraft grounded - emergency declared - descending, experienced sudden loss of pressurization, all masks deployed at fl 380 when cabin alt light came on followed by alt horn sounding and both bleed trip off lights illuminated. flight crew followed bleed trip off in qrh ( quick reference handbook ) and pressurization was re-stored. engine anti ice was on. an emergency was declared and the aircraft landed at denver safely without further incident. * supplemental report : accomplished health checks for left engine per workcard 4414, and right engine per workcard 4415 ; replaced the following com ponents, per applicable workcard : left engine bleed air regulator ( aala202007139003 ), left engine 390 degree precooler

ship 3738 - fumes - after right engine start, fumes in cabin. corrective action : found both hydraulic systems slightly overserviced. had faint smell when starting #2 engine. replaced the right air filter pressure assembly. performed duct burn out. no more odors.

aircraft was grounded : air interrupted back to dfw at 390 right cowl anti ice cmae on. ran the checklist light, did not ex tinguish. declared an emergency. removed and replaced # 2 engine cowl anti ice valve iaw amm 30-21-11. secure connector engine.

aircraft was grounded. when entering runway for takeoff, the left engine high stage light illuminated. removed and replaced high pressure shut-off valve iaw amm 36-11-07 ( aala20170125020 ) and high stage pilot iaw amm 36-11-08. leak and operational check good. nature of condition : warning indication precautionary procedure : aborted takeoff part name : shut-off valve part condition : faulty

after left engine start, left generator drive eicas message displayed. eicas message stayed illuminated for approximately 20 seconds then went away. safety wire broken for left engine drive disk, switch not pushed. found intergrated drive generator on engine 1 low. serviced intergrated drive generator iaw amm 12-13-03, leak check good. no faults at this time.
during borescope inspection found approximately 3 cracked on stage 1 lower pressure turbine ngv 1 segment w4 vanes cracked 3 segment. right & right nr 2 engine per mt.
nr 2 engine right nacelle panel, forward hold open rod lock release collar will not release. removed and replaced the 2 engine forward hold open rod.
